INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',1,1,'Title: Luke writes another book. Theophilus, the first book that I write was part of all of the things that Jesus does and all of the things that he teaches.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',1,2,'At that time Jesus did all of these things. At that time that he is born at that time that he is carried to heaven before Jesus went to heaven, he talked to the apostles that he chose. The Holy Spirit helped Jesus tell these apostles about the things that they should do.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',1,3,'<<Jesus died. After Jesus died, he rose from the dead.>> After Jesus suffered, he showed himself to his representatives during forty days. Before Jesus went up to heaven, during those forty days he proved many times to those representatives that he was alive. <<He ate meals with those people. And he talked to those people. So the representatives knew that Jesus was alive.>> Jesus spoke to those representatives about God''s kingdom. And he told those representatives that God ruled his people.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',1,4,'One day while Jesus was eating with the apostles, he told them to stay in Jerusalem. He said to the apostles, Wait here until you receive the gift that the Father promised you that he would send to you. Remember that previously I told you about this gift.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',1,5,'John baptized people with water. But after a few days you''ll be baptized with the Holy Spirit.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',1,6,'Title: Jesus is carried to heaven. One day the apostles were with Jesus and asked him, Lord, will you give the kingdom of Israel to the Israelites now?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',1,7,'Jesus said to the apostles, The Father has many authority. Only the Father is able to choose the days when these things will happen. You aren''t able to know the dates when these things will happen.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',1,8,'But the Holy Spirit will come to you and give power to you. You''ll tell people about me. You''ll tell all of the people who live in Jerusalem, all of the people who live in Judea, all of the people who live in Samaria, and all of the people who live on the earth about me.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',1,9,'After Jesus said these words, he was lifted to heaven in front of the representatives by God. And the representatives that thing saw happen. Then they stopped seeing Jesus because a cloud covered him.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',1,10,'While Jesus was going, the representatives looked hard at the sky. Suddenly they saw two men who wore white clothes. Those men stood near the representatives. <<They were servants who came from God.>>');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',1,11,'These men said, Men who are from Galilee, why are you standing here? Why are you looking at the sky? You saw Jesus carrying to heaven. Jesus will return from the sky to the earth.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',1,12,'Title: Jesus'' representatives choose Matthias so that he would replace Judas. Then Jesus'' representatives left the Mount of Olives and returned to Jerusalem. The distance that was between Jerusalem and the Mount of Olives was about it.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',1,13,'After the apostles entered the city, they went to the room where they were staying. They were Peter, John, James, Andrew, Philip, Thomas, Bartholomew, Matthew, James, who was Alphaeus'' son, Simon, whom people called Zealot, and Judas, who was James'' son.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',1,14,'All of these apostles were in that room. They were always praying. Certain women also were with these apostles. And Mary, who was Jesus'' mother, and his younger brothers also were in that room with the apostles.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',1,15,'After a few days all of the Christians met. They came to this meeting. Then Peter stood up.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',1,16,'And Peter said, Brothers and sisters, the Holy Spirit said in the scriptures through David that these things have to happen. The Holy Spirit was talking about Judas, who was an apostle.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',1,17,'Judas served Jesus with us. The Holy Spirit said that Judas will lead men to Jesus so that they could arrest him.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',1,18,'Judas received a reward money because of the evil thing he did the thing. And he bought a field for that money. But he fell in that field. Judas'' body broke so that it could open. <<And Judas died.>> Parts of Judas'' body came out immediately from it.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',1,19,'All of the people who lived in Jerusalem found out about this event. So they called that field ''Akeldama'' in their language. Akeldama means the field of blood.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',1,20,'Then Peter said, The Holy Spirit wrote about these things to the book named Psalms. The Holy Spirit wrote, People shouldn''t go near that man''s land. And people shouldn''t live on that land. The Holy Spirit also wrote, Allow another man to do that man''s work. Footnote: The Holy Spirit wrote these things in Psalms 69:25 and in Psalms 109:8.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',1,21,'Therefore, we need to choose another man who was with us during the whole time when the Lord was with us.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',1,22,'At that time that man was with us until the day when Jesus was carried from us to heaven. At that time that John baptized people');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',1,23,'So the apostles told two men to stand in front of the people. One man''s name was Joseph. People called that man Barsabbas. They also called that man Justus. And the other man''s name was Matthias.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',1,24,'Then the apostles prayed. One of them said, Lord, you know all of people''s thoughts. Show us the man that you''ll choose. Then that man will do this work.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',1,25,'Judas stopped doing this work and went to the place where you send him. Lord, show us the man who should become an apostle.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',1,26,'Then the representatives used stones that had marks <<to choose the man who should replace Judas>>. And the stone that showed the Lord chose Matthias fell from the bag. So Matthias became a representative and joined them.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,1,'Title: The Holy Spirit comes. When the day was the day that was after a Passover, all of the people who believed in Jesus met in one place.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,2,'Then the Holy Spirit will be with the disciples. He''ll give power to Jesus'' disciples and lead them to other countries. Then the disciples will tell other people about Jesus'' kingdom.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,3,'The disciples will continue telling people about Jesus until he returns to the earth. So the Spirit came to Jesus'' disciples in Jerusalem. And the disciples became like a new temple. Earlier the prophets promised the Israelites that these things would happen.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,4,'But the leaders of Jerusalem didn''t agree with Jesus'' disciples. So they ordered people to start killing the Christians. But when the leaders started killing Christians, the Spirit caused the Jews who were living in Jerusalem to leave it. Then Gentiles started believing in Jesus.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,5,'In the beginning God created the heavens and the earth. Nothing existed on the earth. And darkness was covering the deep water. Then he said, Let there be light. Then there was light.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,6,'On the second day God separated the water to make the seas and the sky. On the third day he created land so that trees and plants could grow. Will we see land again? Yes. We''ll certainly see land again. The next day God put the sun, the moon, and the stars in the sky.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,7,'And on the fifth day God made all of the creatures that were in the sea and in the air. And on the sixth day he made all of the creatures that walked on the ground. And then he made us to live in a beautiful garden. But Adam and Eve didn''t obey God. They ate the fruit that God told them not to eat.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,8,'Then Adam and Eve learned about good things and evil things. After Cain killed Abel, God has seen too many evil people. People choose bad things and decide to do evil things. So God caused this flood to happen.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,9,'<<We are different from areas.>> Some of us live Media, and Elam in. Some of us live Judea, and Asia in Mesopotamia.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,10,'Some of us live, Egypt, and the areas Libya, which is near Cyrene named city, in. And some of us are visiting Jerusalem.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,11,'These people include them and them but later who became Jews? And some of us are from Crete and Arabia. We hear these people speaking with our languages. These people are telling us about the great things God has done the things!');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,12,'All of those Jews were amazed because all of them didn''t understand the things the things were happening. They asked each other, What do they mean?.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,13,'But other people <<that in the crowd>> laughed at the followers. They said, These people drank too much wine.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,14,'Title: Peter speaks. Then Peter and the 11 other representatives moved to a place where near the crowd. Peter spoke to the crowd using a loud voice. He said, Jews, I''ll explain these things. So listen carefully. And the people who are living in Jerusalem, also listen.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,15,'Some of you think that these men are drunk. But these men aren''t drunk. The sun rose only three hours.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,16,'No. <<Today a different thing is happening.>> Many years ago the person who told God''s messages to named Joel spoke about this event.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,17,'Joel said in his book, During the last days <<when that God will judge all of the earth''s people>> he say, I''ll pour my Spirit out in all of places on all of my people. Your sons and your daughters will tell the Lord''s message to people in all of places. And your young men and your young women will see dreams and see them.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,18,'On the servants who include men and women of all of me I''ll pour my Spirit out in those days. These men and these women will tell my message people <<that I said them>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,19,'I''ll cause great things to happen in the sky. Those things will show people certain things will happen very soon. And strange signs will appear on the earth below the sky. Those signs will include blood, fire, and dark smoke.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,20,'God will cause the sun to look like darkness. And the moon will become red dark like blood is red. Then after those things the great day that the Lord will come will happen.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,21,'And all of the people who call the Lord the name <<so that he can help them>> will be saved from their bad actions by God.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,22,'Israel''s people, listen to these words. God proved to you that Jesus, who was from Nazareth named town, was the right person. God showed Jesus was the right person by doing and signs through him. And you know these things because when those things happened, you were with Jesus.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,23,'You gave Jesus to people so that they would take him away. Earlier God decided that that thing will happen. You killed Jesus by using evil men <<that didn''t follow God''s law>>. Those evil men killed Jesus by putting him on a cross.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,24,'But God caused Jesus to rise from the dead. Literal Alternate: God released Jesus from the pain death because it wasn''t possible that it keeps him like soldiers keep a prisoner. Dynamic Alternate: After Jesus suffered many, God released him because it wasn''t possible that he dead.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,25,'Many years, David wrote about the Christ. David said, I saw that the Lord always was in front of me. I''m not afraid. For the Lord is with me.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,26,'Therefore, I the heart am glad and happy. And I the body always have hope <<because I know that you''ll cause it after I die, to rise from the dead>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,27,'For you won''t leave me in the place where dead people''s spirits temporarily go after they die. You won''t allow your body''s special person will decay.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,28,'Literal Alternate: You showed me the paths that will lead life. Dynamic Alternate: You showed <<after I die,>> I lived. End of Alternates. You''ll cause me to be completely happy because I''ll be with you forever.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,29,'Then Peter said, And friends I want to tell clearly you that David, who was our father, died. David the body was buried by people. And David''s grave still is here.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,30,'David told God''s messages to people. Literal Alternate: And he knew that God promised himself him that God would put one David''s children on the chair him in the future. Dynamic Alternate: And David knew that God promised his children him that they would become the king of his people in the future. End of Alternates. God made that promise to show David that he''ll certainly do that.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,31,'David understood the thing God will do the thing in the future. So he said these words about the Christ. David said that <<after the Christ dies,>> he''ll rise from the dead. David said that God won''t leave the Christ in the grave. And David said that God won''t allow the Christ''s body will decay.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,32,'God caused Jesus to rise from the dead. We saw that that thing truly happened.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,33,'Literal Alternate: God honored Jesus by causing him to sit at the right side of him. Dynamic Alternate: God honored Jesus by causing him to rule with him. End of Alternates. Jesus received the Father the Holy Spirit that God promised him that he he would send to God''s people. Jesus uses God''s authority to send that Holy Spirit to us. Literal Alternate: Jesus poured that Holy Spirit out on us. Dynamic Alternate: Jesus completely gave that Holy Spirit to us. End of Alternates. That Holy Spirit caused you all of these things that you saw and to hear.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,34,'For David didn''t go up to heaven <<like Jesus went up there>>. Literal Alternate: David said, The Lord said to himself me, Sit at me right side. Dynamic Alternate: He said, The Lord said to himself me, Rule with me.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,35,'Literal Alternate: Sit at me right side until I put you enemies under you feet. Dynamic Alternate: Rule with me while I completely defeat you enemies.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,36,'Then Peter said, Therefore, all of Israel the people understands this thing. God caused this Jesus, whom you killed by putting him on a cross, to be the Lord and a Christ! <<Jesus is the Christ, about whom David talked.>>');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,37,'When the people heard these words, they were extremely sorry. Those people''s hearts hurt like he hurts. <<For those people helped them kill Jesus.>> They said to Peter and the other representatives, Friends, what us should do?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,38,'Peter answered those people, Change into your thoughts and your actions so that they could please God. Then we''ll dip you in in water because you believe in Jesus the name so that God would forgive your bad actions. Literal Alternate: And you''ll receive the gift that is the Holy Spirit. Dynamic Alternate: And you''ll receive the Holy Spirit that God will give to you.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,39,'God promised did those things all of people that the Lord God will call. Those people include you, your children, and all of them.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,40,'Peter said many other things to warn the people. Literal Alternate: He urgently told the people, That don''t be like this evil time''s people. Dynamic Alternate: He urgently told the people, That don''t be like your Jewish friends who refused to accept Jesus. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: Save you <<by asking God saved you your bad actions>>. Dynamic Alternate: Ask God to save you from your bad actions.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,41,'Then many people believed the message Peter. And the representatives dipped in water those people. Literal Alternate: That day about 3,000 people joined the group of followers. Dynamic Alternate: That day about they became followers.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,42,'Title: The followers meet. The followers regularly met with each other and listened carefully to the things that the representatives taught. They ate meals with each other often and faithfully prayed with each other.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,43,'The representatives did many great things through God''s power and signs <<that showed people he is powerful>>. And all of the people were amazed.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,44,'The followers continued meeting often and put their things in one place so that they could share all of them.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,45,'Sometimes the followers sold a property and other things that belonged to them. And they gave the money <<that they got after they sold those things>> to all of them and who needed it?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,46,'Each day the followers met in the yard of the big building that the Jews honored God. They ate meals with each other in their houses and did those things sincerely.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',2,47,'The followers praised God continuously. All of the people <<that lived in Jerusalem>> feared the followers. And each day the Lord saved many people from their bad actions so that the number followers could increase.');
