INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,1,'Title: Jewish leaders arrest Peter and John. The priests, the leader of the soldiers who guarded the temple, and the Sadducees came to Peter and John. Peter and John were speaking to people.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,2,'Those leaders were very angry with Peter and John because they were teaching people about Jesus. Peter and John were proclaiming that there will be a resurrection like God caused Jesus to rise from the dead.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,3,'Those leaders arrested Peter and John and put them in a prison until the next day because it was the evening.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,4,'But many people who heard the things that Peter and John taught believed in Jesus so the number of men who believed in him became about five thousand.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,5,'The next day chief priests, elders, and Scribes met in Jerusalem.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,6,'Annas, who was the high priest, Caiaphas, John, Alexander, and the high priest''s other relatives also were at that meeting.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,7,'The soldiers of those leaders brought Peter and John to a place that was in front of them. Those leaders asked Peter and John, Who helped you heal that man?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,8,'Then Peter was filled with the Holy Spirit and said to those leaders, Chief priests and elders of the people!');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,9,'You ask us a question because we were kind to a lame man. You ask us to explain how we healed that man.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,10,'Literal Alternate: Then you and all of the Israelites should know that the power the name of Jesus Christ who is from Nazareth healed the man who stands in front of you. Dynamic Alternate: Then you and all of the Israelites should know that the power of Jesus Christ who is from Nazareth healed the man who stands in front of you. End of Alternates. You caused people to crucify Jesus. But <<after Jesus was dead,>> God caused him to rise from the dead.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,11,'Jesus is the stone that God''s book talked about. Literal Alternate: God''s book said, The stone that you rejected became the chief corner <<of the building>> stone. Dynamic Alternate: God''s book said, The stone that you rejected became <<the building''s>> most important stone.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,12,'Only Jesus saves us from our bad actions. We don''t have on the earth another person who is able to save us.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,13,'The leaders of the Jews noticed the courage Peter and John. They knew that Peter and John were ordinary men and that they didn''t learn those things from the Scribes. So they were amazed and realized that those men learned those things from Jesus.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,14,'The leaders saw that the man that God healed stood with Peter and John. So they weren''t able to say something to oppose Peter and John.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,15,'So the leaders of named Sanhedrin the Jews commanded Peter John, and the man to go out from the room where the meeting was. Then they started talking to each other about the things that happened.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,16,'The leaders said, We aren''t able to do something to these men <<to punish them>>. All of the people who live in Jerusalem know that these men performed a great miracle. We aren''t able to say <<to people>> that these men didn''t perform that miracle.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,17,'But we must not allow more people to hear about that miracle. We have to warn Peter and John that if they tell more people about this man, we''ll punish them.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,18,'Then the leaders called Peter and John so that they would come into the room again. Literal Alternate: And they commanded Peter and John never to speak using Jesus'' name and never to teach in it. Dynamic Alternate: And they commanded Peter and John never to speak about this man again and never to teach him again.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,19,'But Peter and John said, Does God think it''s right that we obey you more than it''s right that we obey him? Choose the answer that is right.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,20,'But we must stop telling people about the things that we saw and the things that we heard. <<We won''t stop telling people about the things that Jesus did and the things that he said.>>');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,21,'The leaders warned Peter and John again. Then they allowed Peter and John to leave the place where the meeting was. For because of the people, they didn''t know how they''ll be able to punish Peter and John. All of the people praised God because he healed that man.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,22,'The man that God healed through a miracle was more than forty years old.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,23,'Title: The Christians pray. After the leaders allowed Peter and John to leave that meeting, they returned to the other Christians and told them about all of the things that the chief priests and the elders said to them.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,24,'After those believers heard these things, they started praying to God with each other loudly. They prayed, You''re the Lord, who has all authority. You made heavens the earth and the sea and made all of the things that are in them.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,25,'Literal Alternate: You caused the mouth of your servant named David, who was our ancestor, through the Holy Spirit to say certain things. Dynamic Alternate: You caused your servant named David, who was our ancestor, to say certain things through the Holy Spirit. End of Alternates. David said, Why were the Gentiles very angry? Why did people plan to do certain useless <<evil>> things to me?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,26,'The kings of the earth prepared to oppose the Lord and the man that the Lord chose. And the <<other>> rulers of the earth met with each other and those kings to oppose the Lord and the man that the Lord chose.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,27,'These things certainly happened. Literal Alternate: Herod and Pontius Pilate met with each other in Jerusalem with the Gentiles and with the Israelites to plan to do evil things to your holy servant named Jesus, whom you anointed. Dynamic Alternate: They met with each other in Jerusalem with the Gentiles and with the Israelites to plan to do evil things to Jesus, whom you chose, and who always serves you.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,28,'Literal Alternate: Those people did only the things that your power and you decided many years ago that they''ll do. Dynamic Alternate: They did <<only>> the things that you decided many years ago that they''ll do.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,29,'Lord, when those people say that they''ll do bad things to us, listen to the words that they say. Help us who serve you boldly tell your message.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,30,'Use your power to heal people and to do signs and things that cause them to become very amazed. Literal Alternate: Show people that these things are done by you in the authority of the name your holy servant named Jesus. Dynamic Alternate: Show people that these things are done by you through the authority of Jesus, who is holy, and who always serves you.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,31,'After the believers prayed, the place where they were meeting shook. All of those believers were filled with the Holy Spirit. Then all of them boldly were God''s prophets.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,32,'Title: The Christians share all of their possessions with each other. Literal Alternate: All of the Christians had the same heart and the same mind. Dynamic Alternate: God united all of the Christians with each other so all of them thought the same things and so all of them wanted the same things. End of Alternates. Those believers shared all of their possessions with each other.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,33,'The men that Jesus sent to people so that they would be his representatives for people continued testifying <<to them>> about the resurrection the Lord God''s great power. And a lot of grace was given to all of the believers.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,34,'All of the people who followed Jesus had all of the things that they needed. For sometimes the believers sold land that they owned or houses that they owned. After the believers sold that land and those houses, they brought <<to the apostles>> the money that they received.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,35,'And those believers gave that money to those apostles. And those apostles shared that money with all of the believers who needed it.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,36,'<<A man named>> Joseph who was in the tribe of Levi was from <<the island named>>. The apostles called Joseph Barnabas. Barnabas is a name that means a person who encourages other people.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',4,37,'One day Barnabas sold a field that belonged to him. And he brought to the apostles the money <<that he received>>.');
