INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',6,1,'Title: The men that God sent to people so that they would be Jesus'' representatives for people choose seven believers to take care of the widows. During that time many more people started believing in Jesus. <<Some of those believers were Jews who spoke the Greek. And some of them were Jews who spoke Hebrew.>> The Jews who spoke the Greek started complaining about the Jews who spoke Hebrew. They complained because each day the Jews who spoke Hebrew didn''t give food or money fairly to the widows who spoke the Greek.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',6,2,'<<The twelve men that God sent to people so that they would be for people Jesus'' representatives heard about that problem.>> They told all of those people to meet with those apostles. Those apostles said, It''s wrong that we stopped teaching. We must continue teaching God''s message <<that is about Jesus>> to people. We aren''t able to also give food and money to people.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',6,3,'Choose seven people who are among you. You have to know that each of those people is full of the Holy Spirit. Those people have to also be very wise. We''ll ask those seven people to give food and money to <<poor>> people instead of us giving them to them.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',6,4,'Then we''ll pray <<because we won''t need to do these other things>>. And we''ll also teach God''s message to people.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',6,5,'All of the <<other>> believers agreed to do the thing apostles said the thing. So they chose a man named <<first>>. Had a lot of faith in God. And was full of the Holy Spirit. <<And those believers chose six other men.>> They also chose Philip, and, was from <<the city named>>. When was born, wasn''t a Jew. But later became a Jew.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',6,6,'That group of believers brought these <<seven>> men to those men that God sent to people so that they would be Jesus'' representatives for people. Those apostles put their hands on those men and prayed for each man. <<They gave authority to those men so that they could do that special work.>>');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',6,7,'Those believers continued being God''s prophets <<who was about Jesus>>. So the number of Jesus'' disciples who were in Jerusalem was increasing. Many of the Jewish priests also believed the message that was about Jesus.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',6,8,'Title: Is arrested by the religious leaders. God gave his power and his grace to. Performed wonderful miracles and signs among those people.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',6,9,'But some men opposed. They were from one of the synagogues that were in Jerusalem. People called those men that group of free men. Some of those men were Jews who were from <<a city named>> Cyrene or <<a city named>>. Some of those men were from <<a province named>> Cilicia. And some of those men were from Asia. And those men started arguing with.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',6,10,'But the Holy Spirit helped say wise things. And those men weren''t able to argue with about the words that said.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',6,11,'Then that group of men secretly persuaded some men to lie about. Those men said, We heard blaspheming God and Moses.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',6,12,'When those men said those things, the <<other Jewish>> people became angry with. They included the elders and the Scribes. Then all of them took quickly and brought to the Sanhedrin.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',6,13,'Then those people <<also>> found some bad men so that they would lie about. Those men said, This man says bad things about the temple and about the law of Moses continuously.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',6,14,'We heard saying that Jesus, who is from Nazareth, will destroy this place. Also said that Jesus will tell us not to follow the customs that Moses taught to our ancestors.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Acts',6,15,'All of the Jewish leaders who were in the Sanhedrin and all of the <<other>> people who were sitting in the room where the Sanhedrin met looked at carefully. And those people saw that''s face was very bright like an angel''s face is bright.');
