INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',1,1,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',1,2,'Joel said <<to the elders of the Jews and the people who were living in Judah>>, You who are elders, listen to the LORD''s message! All of the people who live in this land <<named Judah>>, listen to the LORD''s message. Did something that is like this terrible event happen during your lives? Or did something that was like this terrible event happen during your ancestors'' lives?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',1,3,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',1,4,'All of the plants that the first swarm of locusts didn''t eat were eaten by the second swarm of locusts. All of the crops that the second swarm of locusts didn''t eat were eaten by the third swarm of locusts. And all of the crops that the third swarm of locusts didn''t eat were eaten by the fourth swarm of locusts.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',1,5,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',1,6,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',1,7,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',1,8,'Mourn like a virgin mourns because the man that she''ll marry died. That virgin wears clothes made of the sackcloth. Act like that virgin acts.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',1,9,'People aren''t able to give grain and wine to the LORD in his temple because they don''t have them. The priests who serve the LORD in his temple are mourning. Footnote: In this book the LORD calls the temple ''the LORD''s house''.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',1,10,'The fields were destroyed. The ground of those fields is hard and dry. So people aren''t able to harvest grain. They aren''t able to make <<more>> wine. And they aren''t able to make olive oil.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',1,11,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',1,12,'All of the grape plants are dead. And all of the fig trees withered. The poplar trees, the palm trees, the apple trees, and all of the other fruit trees that were in the fields withered. People are very sad because they aren''t able to harvest food. They stopped being happy like those trees stopped living.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',1,13,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',1,14,'Order people to fast. Gather the people so that they would pray to God. Call the elders and all of the people who live in the land named Judah. Those people should come into the temple of the LORD, who is your God. And they should cry out to the LORD <<so that he would help them>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',1,15,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',1,16,'While we were watching those locusts, were our crops eaten? <<We weren''t able to prevent those locusts from eating those crops.>> And when we went to God''s temple, were we joyful?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',1,17,'The seeds that we planted in the ground are shriveled. The big buildings of a farm are empty. So those barns are decaying. For people aren''t able to store grain in those barns because they don''t have it.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',1,18,'The herds of cows are lowing loudly <<because the groups of cattle are hungry>>. And those cows are walking without a purpose. For those cows aren''t able to eat because there is no grass. The flocks of sheep also are suffering <<because the flocks of sheep are hungry>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',1,19,'LORD, I pray to you <<so that you would help us>>! For fire burned all of the grass that was in the wilderness. And it completely burned all of the trees that were in the fields.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',1,20,'The animals that live in the wilderness also cry out to you <<like we cry out to you>>. For all of the streams that those animals usually drink water from don''t have water <<now>>. And all of the grass that was in the fields was destroyed by fire.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,1,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,2,'There will be a lot of darkness on that day. That day will be terrible like a day that is full very dark clouds is terrible. A powerful big army of warriors will invade Judah like the light of the sun that is rising covers mountains. <<The locusts that I told you about are that army.>> There never was an army that was like that army in the past. And there never is an army that is like that army in the future.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,3,'Literal Alternate: A fire burns all of the things that are in front of that army. Literal Alternate: And after that army passes that place, there still is fire. Dynamic Alternate: That army destroys all of the things that are there like fire burns all of the things that are at the place where it''s. End of Alternates. Before that army arrives, the land is like the <<beautiful>> garden of Eden. After that army leaves, the land is like a desert. All of the things that are alive die there.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,4,'The warriors who are in that army seem like horses a war. They run like men who are riding horses move.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,5,'Those warriors are loud like chariots <<that are moving>> are loud. They jump along the mountains. They are loud like fire that is burning dry fields is loud. They are like an extremely big army that is preparing to fight.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,6,'When <<other>> people see this army, they become very afraid of it. Those people''s faces become white <<because they are afraid>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,7,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,8,'Those warriors don''t push each other. Instead, they march straight. They rush past all of the weapons of their enemies. They don''t stop moving.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,9,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,10,'When this army arrives, the ground shakes. The sky <<also>> shakes. The sun and the moon become dark. And the stars stop shining.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,11,'The LORD is leading this army. The number of the LORD''s soldiers is extremely big. And that army, which obeys the LORD''s commands, is very powerful. <<The day when the army comes is the LORD''s day.>> Literal Alternate: The LORD''s day is very terrible! Dynamic Alternate: The day when the LORD judges a person is very terrible! End of Alternates. Is a person able to continue living after that day?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,12,'Title: God told his people to repent. The LORD says to his people, You still have time <<to repent>>. Literal Alternate: Return to me by using your whole heart. Dynamic Alternate: Serve me again by loving me very sincerely. End of Alternates. Fast. Weep. And be sad.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,13,'Joel said, Don''t tear your clothes. Literal Alternate: Instead, tear your hearts. Dynamic Alternate: Instead, because of your evil thoughts, and because of your evil actions, become extremely sad. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: Return to the LORD, who is your God. Dynamic Alternate: Start serving the LORD, who is your God, again. End of Alternates. For the LORD is gentle and merciful. He doesn''t become angry quickly. Instead, he faithfully loves people. And he is always ready <<to forgive>> people instead of causing them to suffer.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,14,'Is it possible that the LORD won''t condemn you? Instead, the LORD might bless you. The LORD might give grain and wine to you so that you would bring offerings of it and offerings of it to him, who is your God.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,15,'<<Priests,>> blow loudly in Zion the trumpet that warns people! Command the people to fast. Call the people so that all of them would pray to the LORD.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,16,'Call all of the people. Make the people become ready they worship the LORD <<religiously>>. <<Also>> gather the old people, the children, and the babies. Let the men who recently married a woman and the women who recently married a man <<also>> leave those people''s houses to come.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,17,'Priests who serve the LORD in his house, weep between the porch and the altar. Pray to the LORD, LORD, be merciful to us. We are your people. Prevent Gentiles from insulting the people who belong to you! Prevent those Gentiles from mocking us. Don''t let those Gentiles say that our God isn''t with us.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,18,'Title: God replies to his people. Then the LORD greatly desired to protect his land. And he felt pity for his people who lived in Judah.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,19,'The LORD replied to his people, I''ll cause the land to produce grain, new wine, and olive oil for you. You''ll have a lot of grain, a lot of new wine, and a lot of olive oil so you''ll be full. I never will again let the people of other nations insult you.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,20,'I''ll cause that army that is coming from the northern region to go from you. I''ll chase that army away so it goes to a very dry and empty desert. I''ll cause the warriors who are in front of that army to die in the Dead Sea. And I will cause the warriors who are in the back of that army to die in the Mediterranean Sea. Those warriors'' bodies will smell terrible. Joel <<said>>, The LORD''s actions are wonderful!');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,21,'Ground, don''t be afraid. <<Instead,>> be joyful. Be very happy. The LORD did wonderful things!');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,22,'Animals that live in fields, don''t be afraid. For the grass that is in the wilderness is becoming green <<again>>. The trees are producing fruit <<again>>. The fig tree and the grapes plants are producing a lot of fruit.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,23,'People of Zion, be happy! Because of the LORD, who is your God, and because of the things that that LORD did for you, be joyful! For the LORD caused the first rain of the season to fall because he is faithful. He caused enough rain to fall on your fields. He caused the rain to fall in the fall and in the spring like he sent it before this time.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,24,'There will be a lot of grain on the threshing floor <<again>>. And there will be a lot of wine and a lot of oil in the big containers that people use to store them <<again>>');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,25,'The LORD <<said>>, I''ll give you those good things that you didn''t have during the years those locusts ate your crops. The first, second, third, and fourth swarms of locusts are my big army that I sent to your land.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,26,'You''ll have more than enough food <<now>>. <<Whenever you eat,>> you''ll <<always>> be full. Literal Alternate: And you''ll praise my name. Dynamic Alternate: And you''ll praise me. End of Alternates. I''m your God, who did wonderful things for you. I never will again let my people be ashamed.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,27,'Then you''ll know that I''m with you in Israel. And you''ll know that I who am the LORD am your God. You''ll know that there is no other God. <<I''m the only true God.>> I never will again let my people be ashamed.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,28,'I''ll send a Holy Spirit me to all of my people after these events. Your sons and your daughters will prophesy. The old people who are among you''ll have dreams that have special meanings. And the young people who are among you''ll see visions.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,29,'Those days I''ll also send the Holy Spirit me to the male servants who are among you and female servants who are among you.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,30,'I''ll put a sign that will cause people to be amazed <<and will warn them>> in the sky and on the earth. There will be blood, fire, and dark smoke.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,31,'The sun will become dark. And the moon will look red like blood is <<red>>. Literal Alternate: Then the LORD''s wonderful and terrible day will happen. Dynamic Alternate: Then the wonderful and terrible day when I''ll judge people will happen.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',2,32,'Literal Alternate: But each person who calls my name so that I would help him will be saved. Dynamic Alternate: But each person who prays to me so that I would help him will be saved. End of Alternates. People will be saved on Mount Zion, which is in <<the city named>> Jerusalem. For I promised I save my people. Those people will be among the people that I choose to save.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',3,1,'Title: God will punish his enemies. The LORD says, In those days I''ll cause the people of Jerusalem and all of the people of Judah to succeed again.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',3,2,'I''ll gather the people of all of the nations and cause them to go down to the Valley of Jehoshaphat. I''ll judge those people there because they treated badly the people of Israel who belong to me. Those people forced my people to live in many different foreign countries. And they divided my land');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',3,3,'Those people cast special lots to choose people among my people to become slaves. They sold the boys me to pay prostitutes. And they sold the girls me to pay for wine that they drank. Footnote: In those days sometimes the Jews and other people cast special lots to know the thing that they should do.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',3,4,'People who live in <<the city named>> Tyre, <<the city named>> Sidon, and the whole region named Philistia, did I harm you? Are you trying to take revenge against me because you think that I have harmed you? Because of the things that you did to my people, if you try to take revenge against me, I''ll take revenge suddenly and quickly against you.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',3,5,'Literal Alternate: For you took the silver that belonged to me <<and was in my house>>. Dynamic Alternate: For you took the silver things that belonged to me <<and were in my house>>. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: And you took the gold that belonged to me <<and was in my house>>. Dynamic Alternate: And you took the gold things that belonged to me <<and were in my house>>. End of Alternates. You took my most valuable things away to put it in your buildings where you worshiped your gods.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',3,6,'You sold the people of Judah and the people of Jerusalem to the Greeks so that you could force those people to live in far places.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',3,7,'But I''ll cause those people to return from the places where they went because you sold them. And I will cause you to suffer like those people suffered <<because they were sold by you>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',3,8,'I''ll cause your sons and your daughters to be sold to the people of Judah. Then the people of Judah will sell those sons and those daughters to the Sabeans who live in a very far place. This message was told to the enemies Judah by the LORD through Joel.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',3,9,'<<Then>> Joel <<said to the people of Judah>>, Proclaim to the foreign nations, Prepare to fight a war! Call your warriors! Command all of your warriors to move toward the battle place! And command all of the nations'' warriors to attack their enemies!');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',3,10,'Cause your big tools that you cut fields to plant seeds there to become swords. And cause the knives you use in your gardens to become poles that have sharp points <<and are weapons>>. All of you who are weak, you should think that you''re powerful warriors!');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',3,11,'All of you, nations that are close, come quickly. And gather in the Valley of Jehoshaphat. And LORD, also send the warriors you <<so that they you would fight those nations'' warriors>>!');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',3,12,'<<And>> the LORD <<says>>, The men all of the nations have to prepare. And the men those nations have to come to the Valley of Jehoshaphat <<to fight>>. For I''ll judge there all of the people who come from the countries that are near Judah. And I will punish those nations.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',3,13,'Those nations are full of evil actions like a winepress is filled with many grapes. And those nations are full of evil actions like stone containers that people store wine in are very full of wine. And those nations are ready to be punished like crops that are in a field are ready to be gathered. So you <<who will punish those people for me>>, punish them like a person harvests crops. And punish those people like a person squeezes grapes.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',3,14,'Joel <<said>>, There will be extremely many people in that valley where the LORD will judge them. Literal Alternate: The LORD''s day will happen soon in that valley that he''ll judge people in. Dynamic Alternate: The day when the LORD will judge those people in that valley will happen soon.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',3,15,'The sun and the moon will become dark. And the stars will stop shining.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',3,16,'The LORD will shout in Zion like a lion roars. The LORD''s voice will be very loud in Jerusalem like a sound that happens with the light that happens during the storm is very loud. Because of the LORD''s voice, the earth and the sky will shake. But the LORD will protect his people. He''ll be like a strong wall by protecting his people.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',3,17,'The LORD <<says>>, Then you''ll know that I, who am the LORD, and who am your God, am in Zion <<with you>>. Zion is my holy hill. Jerusalem will be the holy city <<where evil things never will happen>> me. Enemies never will enter Jerusalem again.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',3,18,'Title: God will bless his people. The LORD <<says>>, That day you''ll receive a lot of fresh wine from the mountains <<where the vineyards are>> and will receive a lot of milk from the cattle of the hills. And all of the streams that are in Judah will be full of water. A spring will flow from the LORD''s temple and give water to the valley where acacia trees grow.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',3,19,'But <<the country named>> Egypt will become a desert. And <<the country named>> Edom will become a terrible empty wilderness. For the warriors Egypt and the warriors Edom attacked the people of <<the land named>> Judah cruelly. Those warriors killed there people who were innocent.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',3,20,'<<But>> there will always be people who live in Jerusalem and other places that are in Judah.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Joel',3,21,'Should I punish the people who killed my people <<who were innocent>>? Joel <<said>>, The LORD lives in Zion.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,1,'Title: The word becomes a human. In the beginning the word is and is with God. And it''s God.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,2,'The word is with God in the beginning.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,3,'All of things existed because of the word. And no things existed without the word.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,4,'Literal Alternate: Life was in the word. Dynamic Alternate: The word gives life to people. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: And that life was the light for all of people. Dynamic Alternate: When the word gives life to people, it''s like a light that causes them to be able to see things that are true.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,5,'And the light shines in the darkness. And the darkness never defeated the light.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,6,'A man named John was sent by God.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,7,'Literal Alternate: God sent John so that he could tell people about the light. Dynamic Alternate: God sent John so that he could tell people about the word that is like light. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: Then through John those people believes in the light. Dynamic Alternate: Then through he those people believes in the word.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,8,'John wasn''t the light. But he came to tell people about the light.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,9,'That word that was like a true light was coming into the earth. And shine all of people');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,10,'The word was in the earth. <<Light>> but although the earth existed through the word, the people who lived there didn''t recognize it.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,11,'The word came to the place where its people lived. But the people who belonged to the word didn''t receive it.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,12,'Literal Alternate: But the word gave the right to all of the people who received it and who believed in the name it? So that those people, become God''s children. Dynamic Alternate: But it caused all of people who completely trusted it to be able to become them.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,13,'People became God''s children because he caused them to be his children. Literal Alternate: They God''s children don''t become give physical birth or a husband the flesh. Dynamic Alternate: They don''t become like God''s children because they are born certain parents because they want to sleep with each other or because a husband wants to have children.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,14,'Literal Alternate: And the word becomes flesh. Dynamic Alternate: It became a human. End of Alternates. And it lived among us. We saw the glory that was of the only son who came from the Father the word. So we know that the word is the only son who came from the Father. The son was full grace and truth. And all of the things that the son told us are true.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,15,'John told about the word. He shouted to the crowds, I told you, That before I was born, a person already is. Therefore, that person is greater than me. Later he''ll come.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,16,'Primary: All of us received more and more grace from the word that was it. Alternate 1: All of us received new grace that replaced itself from the word that was it.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,17,'The Law was given to us through Moses named the prophet by God. But grace and truth came through Jesus Christ. When God sent Jesus Christ to us, and he showed us the truth.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,18,'No person saw God. Literal Alternate: But only the son who was God showed God to us. And who who is in the Father''s arms <<is God?>>? Dynamic Alternate: But only the son who was God showed God to us. And who has an extremely close relationship that is with the Father <<who is God?>>?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,19,'Title: John the Baptist says that he isn''t the Christ. John said these words. The leaders of the Jews sent Jewish priests and Levi''s people from Jerusalem named the city John to ask him him a question Jerusalem named the city. Those people asked John, Who are you?.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,20,'John didn''t refuse to answer that question. He admitted, That I''m not the Christ.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,21,'Those priests and Levi''s people asked John, Then who are you? Are you Elijah named the prophet <<that God''s book said returned>>? John said, I''m not Elijah. Then those priests and Levi''s people asked John, Are you the prophet <<that will be Moses>>? And John answered, No. Footnote: See fifteen eighteen and four five Deuteronomies.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,22,'Then the priests and Levi''s people said to John, Who are you? Tell us the answer so that we could tell it to the people who sent us. What do you say about yourself?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,23,'John answered by saying the words the prophet named Isaiah. Literal Alternate: He said, I''m a voice that is shouting in the desert, Make straight paths for the Lord. Said, I''m shouting in the desert, Prepare you the Lord like people prepare a road an important official.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,24,'Then some people that the Pharisees sent asked John a question.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,25,'Those people said, If you''re not the Christ, or Elijah named the prophet, or the prophet, why do you baptize people?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,26,'John answered those people, I wash you with water <<because you''re repenting>>. But a person who don''t know is standing among you.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,27,'Later that person will come. But I shouldn''t even take off the strings that person''s shoes because I''m less good than many of him.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,28,'These things happened on the other side of the Jordan River in Bethany named a place. That place is the place where John was dipping people.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,29,'Title: John says things about Jesus. The next day, John sees Jesus coming toward him. And John said, Look. That person is God''s lamb Primary: That took their bad action away Alternate 1: He provides them to forgive their sin!');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,30,'That person is the person that I talked about. At that time I said, A man who later will come is greater than me because before I was born, that person is.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,31,'Literal Alternate: Previously I knew that person. Dynamic Alternate: Previously I knew that that person was the Christ. End of Alternates. But I washed people with water so that God would cause Israel them to know that he is the Christ.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,32,'Then John said, I saw the Spirit of God, who looked like a bird that came down from heaven. And that Spirit stayed on that person.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,33,'Literal Alternate: Previously I knew that person. Dynamic Alternate: Previously I knew that that person was the Christ. End of Alternates. But God, who sent me so that I would wash people with water, said to me, You''ll see that the Spirit came down and he stays on that person. That person is the person who will wash with the Holy Spirit.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,34,'And I saw these things <<happening to that person>>. And I say to you that that person is God''s son.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,35,'Title: Jesus calls his first disciples. The next day John was standing with the disciples of them at the Arnon River again.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,36,'When John saw Jesus walking, he said, Look. That person is God''s lamb!');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,37,'When the two disciples heard the words John, they followed Jesus.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,38,'Then Jesus turned around. And when Jesus saw those men following him, he asked them, What do you want? Those men said, Rabbi, where do you stay? (Rabbi named the Hebrew word means teacher.)');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,39,'Jesus answered those men, Come with me. And you''ll see the place where I''m staying. So the two men went with Jesus and saw the place where he was staying. And they stayed for that day with Jesus. Literal Alternate: The time was about the tenth hour. Dynamic Alternate: It was about 4 pm.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,40,'Of the one two men who heard John speaking about Jesus was Andrew named a man. And who followed Jesus? Andrew was Simon''s brother.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,41,'Andrew immediately found his brother Simon and said to him, We found the Messiah. (Messiah named the Hebrew word means Christ.)');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,42,'Then Andrew brought Simon to Jesus. Jesus looked at Simon and said, You''re Simon, who is John''s son. But Cephas will be called ''Simon'' by people. (Cephas named the Aramaic word means Peter named the Greek word. <<And of those both of words mean stone.)>>');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,43,'Title: Jesus calls Philip and. The next day, Jesus decided to go to Galilee named the area. There Jesus found Philip named a man. And Jesus said to Philip, Follow me.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,44,'Philip was from Bethsaida named the town like Andrew and Peter were from Bethsaida.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,45,'Philip found Nathanael and said to him, We found the person that Moses wrote in the laws of about God and the prophets also wrote. That person is the son of Joseph named Jesus, who is from Nazareth.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,46,'Nathanael said to Philip were possible a good thing comes from Nazareth?. Philip answered, Come and see that person. <<So Nathanael went with Philip to meet Jesus.>>');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,47,'When Jesus saw Nathanael coming to him, he said about Nathanael, This person truly is an Israelite who is completely honest.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,48,'Then Nathanael asked Jesus, How do you know me? Jesus answered Nathanael, When you were under a fig tree, before Philip called you, I saw you.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,49,'Then Nathanael said, Rabbi, you''re God''s son. You''re the king of Israel.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,50,'Jesus asked Nathanael, Do you believe <<that I''m the son of God and the king of Israel>> because I told you that when you were under the fig tree, I saw you? You''ll see things that are greater than that.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',1,51,'And Jesus also said to Nathanael, I''m telling you true things. You''ll see that heaven opened by God. And the people, will see. God''s angels went up to the Son of Man and they came down to the Son of Man');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',2,1,'Title: Jesus changes water into wine. On the third day there was a wedding at <<a town named>> Cana, which is in Galilee. Jesus'' mother was at that wedding.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',2,2,'And Jesus and his disciples were invited to come to that wedding <<and went there>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',2,3,'<<The people who came to the wedding ate food. And they drank wine.>> When there was no wine <<because people who were celebrating the wedding drank it>>, Jesus'' mother said to him, There is no more wine. <<Are you able to do something to help these people?>>');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',2,4,'Jesus said to his mother, Woman, why do you tell me about this problem? Literal Alternate: My time hasn''t come yet. Dynamic Alternate: This time isn''t the time when I should show every person the things that I''m able to do.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',2,5,'Jesus'' mother said to the servants, Obey Jesus.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',2,6,'There were six <<big>> stone jars there. Those jars contained water so that the Jews could wash themselves. And then those Jews became clean. Each jar was able to contain about 80 or 120 quarts of water.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',2,7,'Jesus said to the servants, Fill the jars with water. So those servants filled those jars with water until they were completely full.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',2,8,'Then Jesus said to those servants, Take water <<from the jars>> now and take it to the leader of this wedding. So the servants took some of the water to the leader of that wedding <<the jars>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',2,9,'<<The water in those jars changed into wine.>> Then that leader tasted the water that had changed into wine. He didn''t know that the wine came from water. But the servants who took the water knew that the wine came from it. Then that leader called the man who married a woman.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',2,10,'And that leader said <<to the groom>>, Every person serves the best wine <<to the guests>> first. And then after the guests become drunk, every person serves less expensive wine to them. <<But you did differently things.>> You kept the best wine until now.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',2,11,'This thing that Jesus did in Cana of Galilee was the first sign that revealed his glory <<to people>>. And Jesus'' disciples believed in him.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',2,12,'After these events Jesus went to <<a city named>> Capernaum with his mother, his brothers, and his disciples. And those people stayed there for a few days.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',2,13,'Title: Jesus goes to the temple. <<Every year the Jews celebrate the Passover.>> Jesus went to Jerusalem a few days before the day the Passover.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',2,14,'Jesus saw people in the courtyard the temple selling cows, sheep, and doves <<for sacrifices that were for God>>. And Jesus saw people who traded money sitting <<at tables>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',2,15,'Then Jesus made a whip from thin ropes and forced the all sheep and the all cows to leave the courtyard the temple. And Jesus scattered the money of the people who traded it. And he knocked those people''s tables over.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',2,16,'Jesus said to those people who sold doves, Take these things away from here! Stop changing my Father''s house into a market!');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',2,17,'Jesus'' disciples remembered the words that were written <<in God''s book>>. Those words said, I love your house dearly. And that love completely controls me. Footnote: See Psalms 69:9.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',2,18,'Then the Jews asked Jesus, Which sign will you show to us so that we <<would know>> that you have authority to do these things?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',2,19,'Jesus answered those Jews, Destroy this temple. And I will cause this temple to become in three days like a new temple.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',2,20,'The Jews answered, People worked for 46 years to build this temple. Will you build this temple in three days?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',2,21,'But the temple that Jesus talked about was his body.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',2,22,'After God caused Jesus to rise from the dead, the disciples remembered that he said this. And they believed that the scriptures and the words that Jesus said were true.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',2,23,'When Jesus was in Jerusalem to celebrate the Passover feast, many people who saw the signs that he did believed in his name.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',2,24,'But Jesus didn''t trust in those people. For he knew all people <<well>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',2,25,'Jesus didn''t need a person to testify about people him. For Jesus already knew the things that each person thought about.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,1,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,2,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,3,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,4,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,5,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,6,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,7,'You shouldn''t be surprised because I said to you, Literal Alternate: You have to be born again, Dynamic Alternate: You have to be born religiously.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,8,'The wind blows places where it wants to go. You hear the sound the wind. But you don''t know the place that the wind comes from or the place where it goes. Every person who is born through the Spirit is like the wind.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,9,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,10,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,11,'I tell the truth to you. We speak about the things that we know. And we speak about the things that we saw. But you still don''t believe the things that we testify to you about.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,12,'I spoke to you about things that happened on earth. And you don''t believe me. If I speak about things heaven, how will you believe me?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,13,'No person went up to heaven except the person who came down from there. That person is me, the Son of Man.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,14,'I, the Son of Man, must be lifted like Moses lifted the the bronze snake in the desert.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,15,'Then each person who believes in the Son of Man may have eternal life.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,16,'For God loved the people of the earth very much so he gave his only son. Then people who believe in the son won''t die. But they''ll have eternal life.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,17,'For God didn''t send his son to the earth to condemn the people there. But God sent his son to the earth to save the people there through his son.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,18,'The person who believes in the son isn''t condemned by God. But the person who doesn''t believe in the son is already condemned by God because he didn''t believe in God''s only son''s name.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,19,'Because of this reason, people are judged by God. Light came to the earth. But people loved darkness instead of the light because their actions were evil.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,20,'Every person who does evil things hates the light. And he won''t come into the light because he is afraid it will show people the evil things that he did.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,21,'But the person who does right things comes to the light so that people would easily know that he did them through God.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,22,'Title: John testifies Jesus again. After these things happened, Jesus and his disciples went to the land Judea. Jesus stayed with his disciples there and baptized people in water there.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,23,'John was also baptizing people in water at <<a town named>> it was near <<a town named>> because there was a lot of water there. And people were coming to John and baptized in water by him.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,24,'(Before John was put into prison, these things happened.)');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,25,'Some of John''s disciples started arguing with a certain Jew about the things that people should do to become clean religiously.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,26,'Then those disciples came to John and said to him, Rabbi, look. That man who was with you on the other side of Jordan and you spoke about is baptizing people in water. And all people are going to that man.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,27,'After John heard these things, he said, A person is able to receive only the things that are given to him by God, who is in heaven.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,28,'You''re able to testify to people that I said, I''m not the Christ. But I was sent so that I would prepare the path for the Christ.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,29,'The woman who is marrying a man belongs to him. But that groom''s friend waits and listens to sounds to hear him coming. And when that friend hears the voice that groom, he rejoices. <<I''m like that friend.>> Therefore, I rejoice.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,30,'Jesus has to become more important. I have to become less important.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,31,'The person Literal Alternate: Who comes from the highest place Dynamic Alternate: That comes from the place where God is End of Alternates. Is above all people. The person who is from the earth knows about only things that are on there. And he speaks about things of the earth. The person who comes from heaven is above all people.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,32,'That person testifies the things that he saw and the things that he heard. But no person believes the things that that person says.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,33,'The person who believes the things that that person testifies agrees that God says true things.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,34,'For the person that God sent speaks his words because he completely gives the Spirit to that person.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,35,'The Father loves the son Literal Alternate: And put all things into his hands. Dynamic Alternate: And the Father gave authority to the son so that he would rule all things.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',3,36,'The person who believes in the son has eternal life. But the person who doesn''t obey the son won''t have life. Literal Alternate: For God''s wrath stays with that person. Dynamic Alternate: For God will continue being angry with that person.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,1,'Title: Jesus talks with a woman who is from Samaria. The Pharisees heard that the number of Jesus'' disciples was becoming bigger than the number of John''s disciples. And they heard that the number of disciples that Jesus baptized in water was more than the number of disciples that John baptized in water. Jesus learned that the Pharisees heard these things.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,2,'(It wasn''t Jesus who actually baptized people in water. But it was Jesus'' disciples who baptized people in water.)');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,3,'So Jesus left <<the province named>> Judea and traveled toward Galilee again.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,4,'Jesus needed to travel through <<the province named>> Samaria <<to travel to Galilee>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,5,'So Jesus came to a town Samaria named. Was near the land that Jacob gave to his son.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,6,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,7,'A Samaritan woman came <<to the well>> to get water. Jesus said to that woman, Give a drink to me.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,8,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,9,'The Samaritan woman said to Jesus, You''re a Jew. And I''m a Samaritan woman. Why do you ask me for a drink? (For Jews avoid Samaritans.)');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,10,'Jesus said to that woman, If you had known about the gift that God gives to people, and if you had known the person who asked you for a drink, you would have asked him for water. And I, that person, will give you water that causes people to live forever.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,11,'That woman said to Jesus, Master, you don''t have a container. And the well is deep. Where are you able to get this water that causes people to live?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,12,'Are you greater than our ancestor named Jacob, who gave the well to us? Our ancestor named Jacob drank from the well with his sons and his animals.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,13,'Jesus said to that woman, Every person who drinks the water that is from this well will become thirsty again.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,14,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,15,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,16,'Jesus said to the woman, Go and call your husband. And return here <<with your husband>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,17,'The woman said to Jesus, I don''t have a husband. Jesus said to the woman, You were right when you said that you don''t have a husband.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,18,'For you had five husbands. And the man that you live with isn''t your husband. The thing that you said is true.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,19,'The woman said to Jesus, Master, I notice that you''re a prophet.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,20,'Our ancestors worshiped God on this mountain. But you and other Jews say that the place where we have to worship God is in Jerusalem.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,21,'Jesus said to the woman, Woman, believe me. In the future you won''t worship the Father on this mountain or in Jerusalem.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,22,'You and other Samaritans worship God, whom you don''t know. We <<, who are Jews,>> worship God, whom we know, because he revealed the Savior to the Jews.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,23,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,24,'God is a spirit. Literal Alternate: Therefore, people who truly worship God have to worship him in the Spirit and in truth. Dynamic Alternate: Therefore, when those people worship the Father, they have to be people who are controlled by the Spirit and believe the truth.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,25,'The woman said, I know that the Messiah will come. (The Messiah is called the Christ.) When that person comes, he''ll explain all things to us.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,26,'<<Then>> Jesus said to the woman, I AM. I, who am speaking to you, am that person.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,27,'Title: Jesus'' disciples return. At that time Jesus'' disciples returned. And they were surprised because Jesus was talking with a woman. But a person didn''t ask Jesus, What do you want? And a person didn''t ask Jesus, Why are you speaking to that woman?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,28,'Then that woman left her jar that she carried water in. And she returned to <<her>> town. And she said to the people <<who lived in that town>>,');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,29,'Come and meet a man who told me about all of the things that I did. Might this person be the Christ?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,30,'Those people came out from that town and started going to the place where Jesus was.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,31,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,32,'But Jesus said to those disciples, I have food that I eat and you don''t know about.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,33,'Then those disciples said to each other, Did a person bring food to Jesus?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,34,'Jesus said, The person who sent me wants me to do certain work. And I will finish doing that work. Literal Alternate: That work is my food. Dynamic Alternate: When I do that work, I''m happy like a hungry person who eats food is happy.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,35,'Do you say, There still are four months until the time when people harvest crops? Behold. I tell you to open your eyes. And look at the fields! The grain that is in those fields <<already>> is ready so people are able to harvest it. Footnote: Jesus is saying that people are ready to believe in God like grain in the field is ready to be harvested.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,36,'The person who harvests that grain already earns a wage. And he gathers people like people gather crops so that they could receive an eternal life. So the person who plants the seeds and the person who gathers the crop are joyful.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,37,'For people often say, One person plants the seeds. And another person harvests the crop. And these words are true.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,38,'I sent you <<into a field>> so that you would harvest a crop. Previously you didn''t work in the field. Other people worked <<in that field>>. And you''re harvesting a crop that other people planted. Footnote: Jesus is saying that people who tell God''s message to other people are like a person who harvests a crop.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,39,'Title: Many Samaritans believe in Jesus. Many of the Samaritans who lived in that town believed in Jesus because the woman testified, Jesus told me all of the things that I did.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,40,'So when those Samaritans came to Jesus, they were asking him to stay with them. And Jesus stayed <<in that town>> for two days.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,41,'Because of the things that Jesus said <<to those Samaritans>>, many more Samaritans believed in him.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,42,'Those Samaritans said to the woman, We believed in Jesus first because of the words that you said. But we believe in Jesus now because we also heard his words. And we know that this man truly is the person who will save the people of the earth.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,43,'Title: Jesus heals a royal official''s son. After two days Jesus and his disciples left that town and went to Galilee.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,44,'(Earlier Jesus said that prophets aren''t honored in the country them.)');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,45,'When Jesus arrived in Galilee, the people there welcomed him. They saw all of the things that Jesus did at the Passover in Jerusalem <<earlier>>. For they also went to the Passover.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,46,'Then Jesus came again to Cana, which was in Galilee, and earlier in which he changed water into wine. There was a royal official who had a son who was sick in Capernaum there.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,47,'When that official heard that Jesus arrived in Galilee from Judea, he went to him. And that official asked Jesus to come and to heal his son. For that official''s son was almost dead.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,48,'So Jesus said to that official, <<People,>> you won''t believe in me unless you see signs and things that amaze people.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,49,'That official said to Jesus, Master, before my child dies, come.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,50,'Jesus said to that official, Go <<to your house>>. Your son will live. That official believed the words that Jesus said. And he left <<to return to his house>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,51,'While that official was traveling to his house, his servants came to him. And they told that official that his son was alive.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,52,'So that official asked his servants, When did my son start becoming healthy? The servants answered, Yesterday your son stopped having a fever at about.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,53,'Then <<the boy''s>> father knew that this time was the time when Jesus said to him, Your son will live. So the father and his whole family believed in Jesus.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',4,54,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,1,'Title: Jesus heals a man at a pool named Bethesda. Later Jesus went to Jerusalem to celebrate a Jewish feast.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,2,'In Jerusalem named by the Sheep Gate was a pool that was called ''in the Aramaic'' the language by people Bethesda. That pool had groups of five poles that were covered by people with roofs.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,3,'Very many sick people lied under those roofs. Some of them weren''t able to see. Of them were lame and weren''t able to move their bodies.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,4,'Footnote: Copies of this part the scriptures don''t include four verse. But some copies of this part the scriptures include four verse. Verse says four, Those sick people waited the water moved. Sometimes the Lord''s angel came to the pool? And the water. After the angel did this, the first person who went into the pool became healthy.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,5,'A sick man was lying. He was sick for 38 years.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,6,'Jesus saw that man who was lying there. And Jesus knew that that man was sick for many years. Jesus asked that man, Do you want to become healthy?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,7,'<<That sick man answered Jesus, Yes.>> That sick man said, But master, when the water moves, no person helps me go into the pool. Whenever I try to go into the pool, before I go into there, another person goes into there.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,8,'Then Jesus said to that man, Get up and pick up your bed. And walk.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,9,'And that man immediately became healthy. He picked up his bed and started walking. The day that this thing happened was a Sabbath.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,10,'The Jews the leaders said to the man who became healthy, Today is the seventh day of the week. <<When the Jewish leaders saw that that man carried his bed>> the law forbids you carry your bed.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,11,'But that man said to those Jews the leaders, The person who I caused became healthy said to me, Pick up your bed. And walk.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,12,'So those Jews asked that man, Who is he?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,13,'But the man who became healthy didn''t know the person who healed him. For there were many people there. And Jesus already left there.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,14,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,15,'That man went from there and told the Jews the leaders that Jesus healed him.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,16,'Title: Jesus has God''s authority. The Jews the leaders started persecuting Jesus because he did this on the Sabbath.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,17,'Then Jesus said to those Jews, My father is still working. And I''m also working.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,18,'The Jews the leaders more wanted to kill Jesus because he said these things. For Jesus broke the law the Sabbath and also called God ''his father''. So Jesus was saying that he and God were equal.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,19,'So Jesus said to those leaders, I tell you the truth. The son isn''t able to do something alone. He is able to do the things he sees the Father the things doing only. For the things the Father does the things are the things the son also does them.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,20,'For the Father loves the son and shows him each thing he does thing. And the Father will show the son things that that are greater than so that you can be surprised.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,21,'The son gives life to the people that he chooses like the Father causes them rise from the dead.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,22,'For the Father doesn''t judge people. But instead, he trusts the son judge people.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,23,'The father does this so that all of people would honor the son like all of them honor his Father. The person who doesn''t honor the son doesn''t honor his Father who sent the son.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,24,'I tell you the truth. The person who hears my words has life that never end. And who believes in my Father who sent me? He won''t be judged by God. Literal Alternate: Instead, that person moved from death to life. Dynamic Alternate: Instead, he won''t die because God caused him to live forever.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,25,'I tell you the truth. There will be a time when dead people will hear the voice the Son of God. And those people who hear that voice will become alive. That time is now.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,26,'The son''s Father causes people to live. And he caused him to be able to also cause people to live.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,27,'And the son''s Father gives authority to him so that he would judge people. For the son is the Son of Man.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,28,'Because of these surprised words, don''t be. For there will be a time when all of dead people who are in their graves will hear the voice the son.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,29,'And those people will come out from those graves. They''ll be raised by God so that they can live forever. They''ll be raised by God so that they could be punished by him.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,30,'I''m not able to do something alone. I listen to the words that my Father says. And then I use those words to judge people. And when I judge people, I''m fair. For I don''t want to please myself. I want to please the person who sent me.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,31,'Title: Jesus is God''s son. Then if I testify <<to people>> about me, they won''t know whether my words are true or they aren''t true.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,32,'But there is another person who tells about me. And I know that that person''s words that are about me are true.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,33,'You sent people to John the Baptist. And the words that John told you about me about are true.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,34,'I don''t need people to talk about me. But I say these things so that you could be saved by my Father.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,35,'Literal Alternate: John was a lamp that was burning and were shining. Dynamic Alternate: The words that John said are like a lamp that helps you you see clearly things. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: And you rejoiced in the light John. Dynamic Alternate: And you enjoyed at the time when John was living listening to the words him.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,36,'But the words that I say about myself are greater than them. The things I''m doing the things are the things my Father told me to do them. The things I''m doing the things prove that the Father sent me.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,37,'And the Father, who sent me, tells about me. You never heard the voice the Father and never saw him.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,38,'Literal Alternate: And the Father''s words don''t live in you. Dynamic Alternate: And you don''t believe the Father''s words. End of Alternates. For you don''t believe in the person that the Father sent.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,39,'You study the scriptures carefully because you think that they''ll give you life that never end. These scriptures that you study tell about me.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,40,'But you refuse to come to me to receive life <<never end>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,41,'I don''t need people to praise me.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,42,'But I know you. I know that you don''t love God.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,43,'My Father sent me here. I came in my the authority name''s Father. But you didn''t accept me. If another person comes to you in his name, you''ll accept him.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,44,'How are you able to believe in me? You praise each other. But you don''t do things things will cause God to praise you.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,45,'Don''t think that I said about you in front of the Father that you sinned. The person who said about you that you sinned is Moses that you hope that will save you. Dynamic Alternate: You hope that God will save you because you follow Moses. Dynamic Alternate: But because of the things that Moses taught, God said about you that you sinned.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,46,'If you believe the things that Moses taught, you''ll believe me. For Moses wrote about me.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',5,47,'How will you believe the things I say the things because you don''t believe them?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,1,'Title: Jesus provides food for five thousand people. After these things happened, Jesus went across the Sea of Galilee. (The Sea of Galilee is also called by people.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,2,'And a big crowd followed Jesus because the people saw him healing them through God''s power.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,3,'Then Jesus went up a mountain and sat down with his disciples.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,4,'The day was a few days that were before the Jewish holiday named Passover.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,5,'Jesus looked and saw a big crowd coming to him. Then he asked Philip <<, whom the followers of him,>>, Where will we buy enough bread so that these people could eat it?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,6,'Jesus asked Philip this question to test himself. For Jesus already knew the thing he''ll do the thing.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,7,'Philip answered Jesus, Even if we spend the amount of money that a man earns by working for eight months to buy bread, each person <<that here>> will get its only very small piece. Footnote: The amount of money is 200 denarii in a Greek.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,8,'Simon the brother of Peter named Andrew also was a follower. Andrew started talking to Jesus.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,9,'Andrew said, A boy who is here has five pieces of bread grain and of two fish. How will this food it be these many of people?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,10,'Jesus said, Tell the people that they sat down. There was a lot of grass there. And those people sat down. (There were about five thousand men there.)');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,11,'Then Jesus took the pieces of bread and thanked God for it. Then Jesus the followers gave pieces of that bread to the people who were sitting on the grass. Those people ate bread until they were satisfied. Jesus did to the fish the same things that he did to the bread.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,12,'When the people were satisfied, Jesus said to his followers, Don''t waste food. Gather the pieces of bread that the people didn''t eat and them.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,13,'So Jesus'' followers gathered the pieces of bread and them. They filled twelve baskets of the five pieces of bread grain with them.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,14,'Literal Alternate: When the people saw the sign that Jesus did through God''s power, they said, This person truly is the prophet and who will come to the earth? Dynamic Alternate: When the people saw the sign that Jesus did through God''s power, they said, This person truly is the prophet and we expected to come to us.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,15,'Jesus knew that the people planned to come and force he is a king. So he left that place and went to a mountain to be alone.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,16,'Title: Jesus walks on water. That evening Jesus'' disciples went down to the lake <<named Sea of Galilee>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,17,'Jesus'' followers went into a boat and started going to Capernaum across the lake. It already was dark because the time was an evening. And Jesus wasn''t with those followers yet.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,18,'The wind was blowing fiercely. And the waves became big.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,19,'After Jesus'' disciples rowed the boat for about five or six kilometers, they saw that he was near them and that he was walking on the water toward it. And they became afraid.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,20,'Literal Alternate: But Jesus said to those disciples, I AM. Dynamic Alternate: But he said to those disciples, I''m the person that you see. End of Alternates. Don''t be afraid.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,21,'Then Jesus'' disciples welcomed him into the boat. And the boat arrived immediately at the shore where disciples were traveling.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,22,'The next day the people who stayed at the place where people had eaten bread saw that the only boat <<that previously was at the shore>> wasn''t there. They knew that Jesus didn''t go into that boat and that those disciples left that place <<in it>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,23,'Other boats that came from Tiberias arrived near the place where people had eaten the bread that the Lord thanked God for.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,24,'When the crowd realized that Jesus and his disciples weren''t there, the people entered into those boats. And they went to Capernaum to search for Jesus.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,25,'Title: Jesus is the bread that causes people to live. When those people found Jesus on the other side of the lake, they asked him, Rabbi, when did you arrive here?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,26,'Jesus said to those people, I''m telling the truth to you. You don''t search for me because you saw signs <<that only that God was able to do>>. You search for me because you ate the bread that I gave you until you were full.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,27,'Don''t work to get only food that becomes bad. Work to get food that will always be good. This food causes people to live forever. I, the Son of Man, will give this kind of food to you. Literal Alternate: For God, who is the Father, put his sign that shows people that he approves of me, the Son of Man, on the Son of Man. Dynamic Alternate: For God, who is the Father, shows people that he approves of me, the Son of Man.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,28,'So that crowd asked Jesus, What do we have to do to do the things that God wants us to do?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,29,'Jesus answered, The action that God wants you to do is that you believe in me, the person that he sent.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,30,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,31,'Our ancestors ate manna in the wilderness. The following words were written <<in God''s book>>. God gave people bread that came down from heaven so that they could eat. Footnote: See Psalms 78:24.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,32,'Jesus said to the crowd, I''m telling the truth to you. Moses didn''t give you bread that came down from heaven. But my Father gives you true bread that comes down from heaven.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,33,'For God''s bread is the bread that comes from heaven and give a life the earth the people.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,34,'Then those people said <<to Jesus>>, Master, always give this bread to us.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,35,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,36,'But although you see me, you don''t believe in me. I already said this to you.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,37,'All of the people that the Father gives to me will come to me. And I never will reject a person who comes to me.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,38,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,39,'The Father, who sent me, doesn''t want me to lose one of the people that he gives to me. Literal Alternate: On the last day the Father wants me to cause all of those people to rise from the dead. Dynamic Alternate: On the day when God will judge all of the people of the world, the Father wants me to cause all of them to rise from the dead.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,40,'For my Father wants every person who sees me, the Son, and believes in me, the Son, to have an eternal life. Literal Alternate: I''ll cause those people on the last day to rise from the dead. Dynamic Alternate: I''ll cause those people on the day when God will judge all of the people of the world to rise from the dead.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,41,'Then the Jews started complaining about Jesus because he said, I''m the bread that came down from heaven.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,42,'The Jews said, Is this man Jesus, who is Joseph''s son? We know Jesus'' father and his mother. How is Jesus able to say, I came down from heaven?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,43,'But Jesus said, Stop complaining to each other.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,44,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,45,'The prophets wrote in God''s book, All of <<God''s>> people will be taught by him. Every person who hears the words that the Father says and learns the things that he teaches will come to me.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,46,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,47,'I''m telling you the truth. The Christian will live forever.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,48,'Literal Alternate: I''m the bread that causes people to live. Dynamic Alternate: I cause people to live like bread causes people to live.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,49,'Your ancestors ate manna in the wilderness. But they died.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,50,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,51,'I''m the bread that causes people to live. I came from heaven. A person who eats this bread will live forever. This bread is my flesh. And I will give this bread so the people of the world will live.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,52,'Then the Jews started arguing with each other. They said, How is this man able to give his flesh to us so that we could eat it?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,53,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,54,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,55,'For my flesh is true food. And my blood is a true drink.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,56,'The person who eats my flesh and drinks my blood continues staying with me. And I continue staying with that person.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,57,'The Father, who lives, sent me. And because of the Father, I live. So because of me, the person who eats me will live <<forever>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,58,'And I, this bread, came from heaven. Your ancestors ate manna and died. But the person who eats this bread will live forever.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,59,'While Jesus was teaching people in Capernaum, he said these things in the synagogue.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,60,'Title: Many disciples stop following Jesus. After the disciples heard these words, many of them said, It''s difficult for us to accept these words. Who is able to accept these words?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,61,'Jesus knew that his disciples were complaining about his words. And he asked those disciples, Do these words offend you?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,62,'If you see me, the Son of Man, going up to the place that I, the Son of Man, came from, what will you think?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,63,'The Spirit of God causes people to live forever. The flesh isn''t able to cause people to live forever. Literal Alternate: The words that I spoke to you about are a Spirit and a life. Dynamic Alternate: The words that I spoke to you about come from the Spirit. Dynamic Alternate: And those words cause people to live forever.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,64,'But some of you don''t believe in me. For Jesus always knew the disciples who didn''t believe in him and the disciple who will betray Jesus.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,65,'Literal Alternate: And Jesus said, I told you because of this reason that a person isn''t able to come to me unless the Father causes him to be able to come to me. Dynamic Alternate: And he said, I told you because of this reason that a person isn''t able to accept me unless the Father causes him to be able to accept me.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,66,'After Jesus said these words, many of his disciples left him. And they stopped following him.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,67,'Jesus asked the twelve disciples, Do you want to leave like those disciples left?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,68,'Simon answered Jesus, Lord, <<if we leave you,>> to whom will we go? Literal Alternate: You have words that cause us to live forever. Dynamic Alternate: You say words that cause us to live forever.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,69,'And we believe in you and know that you''re God''s holy person.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,70,'Jesus asked the disciples, Did I choose you so that you would be my twelve disciples? Literal Alternate: But one of you is an evil spirit. Dynamic Alternate: But one of you is controlled by an evil spirit.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('John',6,71,'(Jesus was talking about Judas, who was'' son. Judas was one of the twelve disciples. Later he''ll betray Jesus.)');
