INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',1,6,'These wise proverbs will help all people understand wise words, parables, the things that wise people say, and their riddles.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',1,7,'When that person fears the LORD, he is wise. But foolish people despise wisdom and don''t want people to tell them the things that they should do.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',1,8,'Title: People shouldn''t follow evil people. My son, listen to the things that your father teaches to you. And don''t ignore the things that your mother teaches to you.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',1,9,'Literal Alternate: The things that your parents teach to you''ll be like beautiful that is on your head branches or a necklace that is around your neck. Dynamic Alternate: The things that your parents teach to you''ll be like a sign of honor that is on your head or a beautiful necklace that is around your neck.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',1,10,'My son, if sinners tempt you, don''t follow them.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',1,11,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',1,12,'Literal Alternate: Let''s swallow those people while they are alive like the place where some ghosts temporarily go after they die swallows them. Dynamic Alternate: Let''s kill those people while they are healthy like death takes them. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: Let''s completely swallow those people like the grave swallows them. Dynamic Alternate: Let''s send those people to the grave while they are strong.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',1,13,'We''ll take all kinds of valuable things <<from those people>> and fill our houses with them.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',1,14,'Come and join us. And we''ll share with you the things that we steal');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',1,15,'My son, don''t go with those people. Don''t do the things that those people do.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',1,16,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',1,17,'If a person spreads a net at the place where all of the birds see it, it''s useless! <<The birds won''t go into that net.>>');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',1,18,'Those people who sin will fall into their traps. <<So they aren''t like birds that escape. They''ll catch people.>> They''ll die because they''ll catch only themselves!');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',1,19,'So you think about the things that happen to people who gain things by hurting other people. Those people''s violent actions will destroy them.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',1,20,'Title: Wisdom speaks. Wisdom is like a woman who shouts in the street. Wisdom cries out in the square the city loudly.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',1,21,'Wisdom cries out in the noisy places and says its wise words at the gates of the city.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',1,22,'Wisdom asks, You who have little knowledge, how long will you enjoy having little knowledge? How long will people who mock wisdom enjoy mocking it? How long will they hate knowledge?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',1,23,'When I tell you about the bad things that you did, listen to me! Literal Alternate: Then I''ll pour my spirit out on you. Dynamic Alternate: Then I''ll tell you the things that I''m thinking about. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: I''ll cause you to know my words. Dynamic Alternate: I''ll cause you to know my thoughts.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',1,24,'But when I called you, you refused <<to listen to me>>. And when I reached out my hand toward you to invite you to come to me, you ignored me.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',1,25,'You didn''t follow my advice. And when I told you about the bad things that you did, you didn''t listen to me.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',1,26,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',1,27,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',1,28,'Then you''ll call me. But I won''t answer you. You''ll search for me. But you won''t find me.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',1,29,'For you refused to accept knowledge. And you didn''t choose to respect the LORD.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',1,30,'You didn''t accept my advice and refused to allow me to tell you about your sins.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',1,31,'Literal Alternate: So those people will eat the fruit of their actions. Dynamic Alternate: So they''ll get the things that they deserve because of their actions. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: Because of the evil things that people plan to do, they''ll become full. Dynamic Alternate: Because of the evil things that people plan to do, they''ll become like a person who is sick.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',1,32,'People who have little knowledge will die because they refuse to listen to me. They''ll die because they think that they are safe and because they don''t act.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',1,33,'But all of the people who listen to me will be safe. They''ll live peacefully. And they won''t be afraid they''ll be harmed.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',2,1,'Title: Wisdom rewards people who follow it. My son, accept my words. Remember the commands me <<like a person stores extremely valuable things>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',2,2,'Literal Alternate: You turn the ear you toward wisdom. Dynamic Alternate: Listen to wisdom carefully. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: Turn your heart so that you could understand these words. Dynamic Alternate: Try hard to understand these words.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',2,3,'Call the LORD to get wisdom. Cry out <<to the LORD>> so that he would help you understand these words.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',2,4,'<<Eagerly>> search for wisdom like a person searches for silver. Seek wisdom like a person seeks an extremely valuable thing that was hidden.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',2,5,'Then you''ll understand you respect the LORD. And you''ll learn that you know God.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',2,6,'For <<only>> the LORD gives wisdom <<to people>>. Literal Alternate: The words that come from the LORD''s mouth cause us to know things and to understand things. Dynamic Alternate: The LORD''s words cause us to know things and to understand things.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',2,7,'The LORD preserves good advice righteous people. Literal Alternate: He is the good people''s shield. Dynamic Alternate: He protects good people like a shield protects a soldier.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',2,8,'Primary: The LORD guards just people''s lives. Alternate 1: The LORD causes things that happen to be just. End of Alternates. He protects the lives of people who are faithful <<to him>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',2,9,'<<So you should search for wisdom.>> Then you''ll understand the things that are righteous, just, and fair. Literal Alternate: And you''ll know each good path. Dynamic Alternate: And you''ll know the good things that you should do.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',2,10,'Literal Alternate: For wisdom will enter your heart. Dynamic Alternate: For you''ll become wise. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: And knowledge <<the things that the LORD wants>> will please your soul.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',2,11,'Literal Alternate: The good choices you''ll protect you. Dynamic Alternate: You''ll be safe because of the good choices you. End of Alternates. The things that you understand about the things that the LORD wants you to do will guard you.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',2,12,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',2,13,'Literal Alternate: Those people left the straight paths. Dynamic Alternate: They stopped doing good things. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: And they walk in darkness. Dynamic Alternate: And they do evil things.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',2,14,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',2,15,'Literal Alternate: Those people''s paths aren''t straight. Dynamic Alternate: Those people do wrong things. End of Alternates. And they aren''t honest.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',2,16,'Wisdom will also save you from the sinful woman. It will save you from the woman who isn''t faithful to her husband and says words that please you <<to tempt you>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',2,17,'That woman leaves the husband that she married when she was young. <<When that woman married her husband, she said that she''ll be faithful to him.>> She ignores <<now>> the covenant that she made in front of God.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',2,18,'Literal Alternate: The path that leads to that woman''s house leads to death early. Dynamic Alternate: When a person goes to that woman''s house, his actions will lead to death. End of Alternates. A person who follows that woman goes to the dead people''s place.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',2,19,'Literal Alternate: No man who goes to that woman returns <<to his earlier life>>. Dynamic Alternate: No man who sleeps with that woman will live again like before he met her, he lived. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: No man who goes to that woman will walk on the paths life again. Dynamic Alternate: No man who sleeps with that woman will live again happily.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',2,20,'<<But wisdom will help you.>> So <<if you follow wisdom,>> you''ll do good things like good people do good things. Literal Alternate: You''ll continue walking on the righteous people''s paths. Dynamic Alternate: You''ll continue living like good people live.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',2,21,'For the righteous people will live in the land. Blameless people will stay in the land.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',2,22,'Literal Alternate: But evil people will be cut off from the land. Dynamic Alternate: But they''ll be taken away from the land. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: They''ll be pulled from the land. Dynamic Alternate: They''ll be taken away from the land.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,1,'Title: Solomon advises young people. Solomon''s son, don''t forget about the things that I teach you about. Instead, keep the commands me in the mind you.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,2,'These instructions will cause you to live for many years and to be successful and peaceful.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,3,'Literal Alternate: Don''t let love leave you. Dynamic Alternate: Don''t stop loving people. End of Alternates. And don''t stop being faithful. Do these things like a person puts a necklace around his neck. Literal Alternate: Write these qualities on the tablet of your heart. Dynamic Alternate: Remember these things in your heart like a person writes them in a book.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,4,'Then you''ll be respected and please both God and people.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,5,'Literal Alternate: Trust in the LORD in the mind of all of you. Dynamic Alternate: Completely trust in the LORD. End of Alternates. And don''t depend on the things that you understand.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,6,'Always honor the LORD <<obeyed him>>. Literal Alternate: Then the LORD will cause the paths where you walk to be straight. Dynamic Alternate: Then he''ll help you do the things that you should do like people cause a road to be straight so that they could travel there easily.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,7,'Don''t think that you''re extremely wise. Instead, respect the LORD and refuse to do evil things.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,8,'Then your body will be healthy. Literal Alternate: And you''ll have food for your bones. Dynamic Alternate: And your bones will be strong.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,9,'Honor the LORD by giving good things to him your and the first crops that you produced wealth.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,10,'Then the buildings that you store crops will be full. Literal Alternate: And wine will flow from the tops of your containers that contain it. Dynamic Alternate: And the LORD will fill your containers with it.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,11,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,12,'For the LORD judges the people that he loves like a father judges a son who pleases him.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,13,'The person who finds wisdom is blessed. He is blessed by the LORD.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,14,'Literal Alternate: The profit that a person gets because of wisdom is better than it. Dynamic Alternate: Wisdom is more valuable than silver. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: The profit that a person gets because of wisdom is better than it. Dynamic Alternate: Wisdom is more valuable than gold.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,15,'Wisdom is more precious than jewels. No other thing that you might want is valuable like wisdom is valuable.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,16,'Literal Alternate: Wisdom offers give you life of many years its right hand. Dynamic Alternate: It offers cause you live for many years. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: It offers give you wealth its left hand and honor. Dynamic Alternate: It offers cause you have wealth and honor.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,17,'Wisdom will cause your life to be pleasant. Literal Alternate: And all of the paths wisdom are peaceful. Dynamic Alternate: And wisdom will cause your life to be peaceful.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,18,'Literal Alternate: Wisdom is a tree of life for the people who grasp it. Dynamic Alternate: It gives life to the people who use it like a tree gives life by producing fruit. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: All of the people who hold wisdom securely will be blessed. Dynamic Alternate: All of the people who regularly use wisdom will be blessed.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,19,'Literal Alternate: The LORD put the earth on its place by using wisdom. Dynamic Alternate: Wisdom the LORD used made the earth. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: The LORD put heavens on the place heavens by using skill. Dynamic Alternate: Skill the LORD used made heavens.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,20,'The LORD caused the deep water to flow by using the knowledge him. And he caused water to come from the clouds.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,21,'Literal Alternate: Solomon''s son, stop looking at wisdom. Dynamic Alternate: Solomon''s son, never forget about wisdom. End of Alternates. And continue making good plans and good decisions.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,22,'Good plans and good decisions will cause you to live. They''ll be like a beautiful chain that is around your neck.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,23,'Then you''ll walk safely. Literal Alternate: Nothing will hurt your foot. Dynamic Alternate: Nothing will hurt you.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,24,'When you lay down, you won''t be afraid. Literal Alternate: When you lay down, you sleep will be sweet. Dynamic Alternate: When you lay down, you''ll sleep peacefully.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,25,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,26,'For the LORD will cause you to be safe. Literal Alternate: The LORD will prevent a trap from your foot being caught. Dynamic Alternate: He''ll prevent a person from hurting you like a trap catches an animal by grabbing him.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,27,'Whenever you''re able to act, do good things for the people that you should help.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,28,'<<A person might ask you give something him.>> When you have the thing that you should give to a person, don''t say to him, Later return to me. And I will give that thing to you.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,29,'Don''t plot to hurt the neighbor who lives near you and that trusts you.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,30,'If a person didn''t hurt you, don''t say for no good reason that he sinned.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,31,'Don''t want to live like a violent person lives. Don''t choose to do the things that that person does.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,32,'For the LORD detests perverse people. But he is righteous people''s friend.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,33,'The LORD curses evil people''s houses. But he blesses righteous people''s houses.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,34,'The LORD mocks the people who mock him. But he treats the humble people graciously.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',3,35,'Wise people inherit honor. But foolish people will be ashamed.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',4,1,'Title: Wisdom is important. Literal Alternate: My sons, listen to the things that I, a father, teach you. Dynamic Alternate: Young people, listen to me. Dynamic Alternate: Listen to the things that I, a father, teach you. End of Alternates. Listen to me carefully so that you would understand those things.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',4,2,'For the things that I''m teaching you about are good. So don''t abandon those things.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',4,3,'Previously I was a young boy in my father''s house. My mother loved me like she loves an only child.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',4,4,'Then my father taught things to me. Literal Alternate: My father said, Grab my words with all of your heart. Dynamic Alternate: He said, Remember my words in your heart like a person grabs an object with his hand tightly. End of Alternates. Keep my commands. Then you''ll live.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',4,5,'Get wisdom and understand things. Don''t forget about my words. Literal Alternate: And don''t turn my words. Dynamic Alternate: And don''t ignore my words.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',4,6,'Don''t abandon wisdom. Then wisdom will protect you. Love wisdom. Then wisdom will guard you.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',4,7,'Wisdom is the most important characteristic <<that you should have>>. So get wisdom. Even if you need to pay all of the things that you have, learn you understand them.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',4,8,'Think that wisdom is very valuable. Then wisdom will cause you to be great. Literal Alternate: Hug wisdom. Then wisdom will honor you. Dynamic Alternate: Keep wisdom like a person hugs a person that he loves. End of Alternates. Then wisdom will cause people to honor you.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',4,9,'Literal Alternate: Wisdom will put a beautiful circle on your head. Dynamic Alternate: It will be like a sign of honor that is on your head. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: It will give a glorious crown to you. Dynamic Alternate: It will be like a glorious crown.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',4,10,'My son, listen to me. Accept the things that I say. Then you''ll live for many years.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',4,11,'I teach you how to live wisely. Dynamic Alternate: You''ll be like a person who is walking. End of Alternates. I lead you on straight paths.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',4,12,'When you walk through life, nothing will cause you to stop walking. Even if you run, you won''t fall down.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',4,13,'Literal Alternate: Hold tightly the things that you learned. Dynamic Alternate: Remember the things that you learned like a person holds important things tightly. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: You guard those things. Dynamic Alternate: You keep those things well like a person guards valuable things. End of Alternates. For those things cause you to live.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',4,14,'Literal Alternate: Don''t walk on evil people''s path. Dynamic Alternate: Don''t follow evil people. End of Alternates. Don''t do the things that evil people do.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',4,15,'Literal Alternate: Avoid that path. Dynamic Alternate: Stay away from those things like a person avoids a bad path. End of Alternates. Don''t travel on that path. Turn that path. And you continue walking.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',4,16,'For evil people aren''t able to sleep easily until they do evil things. Literal Alternate: They aren''t able to rest easily until they cause a person to fall down. Dynamic Alternate: They aren''t able to rest easily until they hurt a person.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',4,17,'Those people do evil things like people eat bread. And they do violent things like people drink wine.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',4,18,'Literal Alternate: But righteous people''s path is like the light of the sun that rises in the morning. Dynamic Alternate: But righteous people''s lives are like the light of the sun that rises in the morning. End of Alternates. That light continues becoming brighter until the day is completely bright.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',4,19,'Evil people''s lives are like total darkness. Literal Alternate: Those people don''t know the reason that they fall. Dynamic Alternate: They don''t know the reason that they have trouble.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',4,20,'My son, listen carefully to the things that I say. Literal Alternate: Turn your ear so that you can hear my words. Dynamic Alternate: Listen to my words carefully like a person turns his ear toward a person who is speaking.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',4,21,'Literal Alternate: Never stop looking at my words. Dynamic Alternate: Never stop thinking about my words. End of Alternates. Keep those words in your heart.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',4,22,'For those words cause the people who find them to live. And those words cause a person''s whole body to be healthy.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',4,23,'Literal Alternate: So guard your heart carefully. Dynamic Alternate: So be careful so that you wouldn''t think about bad thoughts. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: For your life flows from your heart. Dynamic Alternate: For your thoughts affect all of the things that you do.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',4,24,'Literal Alternate: Don''t use your mouth to lie. Dynamic Alternate: Don''t lie. End of Alternates. Never say things that aren''t true.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',4,25,'Literal Alternate: Your eyes should look straight. Literal Alternate: Look at the things that are in front of you. Dynamic Alternate: You should think about the things that you should do like a person looks at the things that are in front of him <<to he sees the place where he is going>> straight.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',4,26,'Literal Alternate: Think carefully about the paths where you walk. Dynamic Alternate: Think carefully about the things that you do like a person thinks about the paths where he''ll walk. End of Alternates. Then your life will be safe.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',4,27,'Don''t turn toward the right side or the left side. Stay away from evil things.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',5,1,'Title: A person should sleep with only a person who is his wife or his husband. My son, listen to my wisdom carefully. Turn your ear toward the sound of my wise words.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',5,2,'Then you''ll be able to make good decisions. Literal Alternate: And your lips will speak about the things that you know. Dynamic Alternate: And you''ll speak about the things that you know.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',5,3,'Literal Alternate: Honey falls from the lips of a woman who commits adultery. Dynamic Alternate: The words of a woman who commits adultery might please a man like honey pleases a person. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: That woman''s words are smoother than oil. Dynamic Alternate: That man might listen easily to that woman''s words that are like smooth oil.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',5,4,'Literal Alternate: But finally that woman will be bitter like the wormwood is bitter. Dynamic Alternate: But finally she''ll cause you to be bitter like the wormwood tastes bitter. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: And she''ll be sharp like a sword that has two edges is sharp. Dynamic Alternate: And she''ll cause you to have pain like a sharp sword that has two edges might cut you.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',5,5,'Literal Alternate: That woman''s feet go down to death. Dynamic Alternate: The things that that woman does lead death. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: That woman''s steps lead to the place where some ghosts temporarily go after those people die. Dynamic Alternate: That woman is going to dead people''s place.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',5,6,'Literal Alternate: That woman doesn''t think about the path that leads life. Dynamic Alternate: She doesn''t think about the things that she should do so that she would live. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: She doesn''t know that she wanders toward wrong directions. Dynamic Alternate: She doesn''t know that she is like a person who wanders toward wrong directions.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',5,7,'So my sons, listen to me. Literal Alternate: Don''t turn the words of my mouth. Dynamic Alternate: Don''t ignore the things that I say.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',5,8,'Stay away from that woman. Don''t go near the door of that woman''s house.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',5,9,'If you go to that woman, other people will receive the honor that you should have. Literal Alternate: A cruel person will take the best years your life. Dynamic Alternate: A cruel person will take the things that you gained during the best years your life.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',5,10,'Strangers will enjoy your wealth. Another person will take to his house the things that you got because you worked hard.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',5,11,'At the end of your life when the flesh you and your body are weak, <<and when you die soon,>> you''ll cry out.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',5,12,'Then you''ll say, I hated the instruction people who were teaching me that I act correctly. Literal Alternate: My heart refused to listen to people who told me about the bad things that I did. Dynamic Alternate: In my heart I refused to listen to people who told me about the bad things that I did.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',5,13,'I didn''t obey the people who taught things to me. I didn''t turn my ear toward the people who taught me about the sound things.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',5,14,'And when I was in front of the whole group of people, I was almost destroyed by my actions.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',5,15,'Literal Alternate: Drink water from only your container. Dynamic Alternate: Be faithful to your wife like you drink only water that belongs to you. End of Alternates. Drink the fresh water that comes from your well.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',5,16,'Should your water flow into the street? Literal Alternate: Should your streams flow in public squares? Dynamic Alternate: Don''t be like a stream that other women drink from.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',5,17,'Your water should belong to only you. You shouldn''t share your water with strangers.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',5,18,'Literal Alternate: May your spring be happy. Dynamic Alternate: May your wife who is like your spring be happy. End of Alternates. Enjoy the wife that you married when you were young.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',5,19,'Your wife is like a beautiful deer who loves you. Let your wife''s breasts always satisfy you. Let your wife''s love cause you to become excited.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',5,20,'My son, why should a woman who commits adultery cause you to become excited? Why should you hug the breasts a woman who isn''t your wife?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',5,21,'For the LORD sees all of the things that you do. He examines the paths all of you.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',5,22,'An evil person''s sins will catch him in a trap. Literal Alternate: That person will be tied with the ropes his sins. Dynamic Alternate: That person''s sins will be like ropes that tie him.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',5,23,'That person will die because he doesn''t control himself. He''ll go on wrong paths because he is extremely foolish.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,1,'Title: Solomon warns people not to be foolish. My son, perhaps your neighbor borrowed money from a person. And you agreed if your neighbor weren''t able to return that money, to pay it to that person. And you shook that person''s hand <<to show him that you agreed to do this>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,2,'The things that you have said are a trap. <<If your neighbor weren''t able to return that money, you would need to pay it.>> Your words have caught you.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,3,'So do this to release yourself. Literal Alternate: Go immediately to your neighbor because you''re in his hands. Dynamic Alternate: Go immediately to your neighbor because he controls you now. End of Alternates. Don''t think that you''re more important than other people. And urgently beg your neighbor <<to release you from your promise>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,4,'Don''t sleep. Don''t let your eyes rest.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,5,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,6,'You, lazy person, go to the ants. Watch the things that those ants do. And become wise!');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,7,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,8,'But ants store their food in the summer. When that food is ready, ants gather it <<so that they could eat it in the winter>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,9,'Lazy person, how long will you lie in a bed? When will you sleep? And when will you get up?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,10,'You think, I''ll sleep for only a few hours. I''ll sleep for only a few minutes now. I''ll put my hands on my chest so that I can rest.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,11,'Then you''ll become poor like a thief attacked you. You''ll lose the things that you have like a man who had weapons stole your things.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,12,'At all of the places where the person who is worthless and is evil goes the person who is worthless and is evil deceives people.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,13,'That person closes one of his eyes for about a second <<while he looks at his friends>>. He makes a sign by moving his feet. And he points to his fingers at things. <<He does these things to show his friends the things that he wants to do he is showing them to the people that he deceives.>>');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,14,'That person plots in his heart to do evil things. He always causes people to oppose each other.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,15,'Therefore, suddenly that person will have a many disaster. Suddenly he''ll be destroyed. And no person will be able to save that person.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,16,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,17,'Those things are proud eyes, a tongue that lies, hands that kill people who are innocent,');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,18,'A heart that plans to do evil things, feet that run quickly to do evil things,');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,19,'A person who lies when he testifies another person, and a person who causes brothers and sisters to oppose each other.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,20,'Title: Solomon again warns people not to commit adultery. My son, keep your father''s command and don''t ignore the things that your mother teaches to you.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,21,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,22,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,23,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,24,'These things will help you stay away from evil women. Literal Alternate: These things will protect you from the smooth words of a woman who isn''t faithful to her husband. Dynamic Alternate: These things will protect you from the words of a woman who isn''t faithful to her husband that might please you.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,25,'Don''t lust after that woman because she is beautiful. Literal Alternate: Don''t let that woman''s eyes capture you. Dynamic Alternate: Don''t let that woman capture you by looking at you with her eyes.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,26,'For a person is able to sleep with a prostitute by giving a piece of bread to her. Literal Alternate: But a woman who commits adultery hunts your life. Dynamic Alternate: But she''ll cause you to die.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,27,'Is a person able to carry hot coal against his chest so it doesn''t burn his clothes?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,28,'Is a person able to walk on hot coal so it doesn''t burn his feet?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,29,'A man who sleeps with another man''s wife is like those people. Literal Alternate: He''ll be punished by her husband severely. Dynamic Alternate: That man will be punished by that woman''s husband severely.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,30,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,31,'Literal Alternate: If the thief is caught by a person, he has to pay seven times the price of that food. Dynamic Alternate: If that thief is caught by a person, he has to pay several times the price of that food. End of Alternates. Even if that thief has to pay all of the things that he owns, he''ll pay that amount.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,32,'But a man who commits adultery is extremely stupid. He destroys his life.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,33,'People will hit that man and publicly cause him to become ashamed. That man never will stop being ashamed.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,34,'For a husband who is jealous will become extremely angry because another man slept with his wife. When that husband takes revenge against that man, he won''t be merciful.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',6,35,'That husband won''t accept a payment. Even if that gift is extremely valuable, he won''t be satisfied by it.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',7,1,'Title: Solomon warns his son about women who commit adultery. My son, keep my words. Remember the commands me <<like a person stores extremely valuable things>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',7,2,'Keep my commands. Then you''ll live. Guard the things that I teach to you like you protect your eyes.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',7,3,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',7,4,'Say to wisdom, You''re my sister. Treat the things that you understand like you treat your closest friend.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',7,5,'Those things will help you stay away from a woman who commits adultery. Those things will help you stay away from the woman who isn''t faithful to her husband and says words that please you <<to cause you to sleep with her>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',7,6,'One day at the window my house I looked there through the pieces of wood of the window frame.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',7,7,'I saw people who didn''t have a lot of knowledge. I noticed a foolish young man among other young men.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',7,8,'That young man was walking on the street near the corner that a certain woman lived at. He was going toward that woman''s house.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',7,9,'The time was the time that was during the evening and when the sky was becoming less bright. The sky started becoming dark like the night is dark.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',7,10,'Then that woman came out from her house to meet that man. She wore clothes that were like the clothes that a prostitute wears. She planned to hide from her husband.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',7,11,'(That woman is rebellious and loud and doesn''t do the things that her husband wants her to do. Literal Alternate: That woman''s feet never stay at her house. Dynamic Alternate: That woman never is at her house.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',7,12,'At one time that woman is in the street. At another time she is in the city square. She waits at the corners the streets <<to find men>>.)');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',7,13,'That woman grabbed that man and kissed him. When that woman spoke to that man, she wasn''t ashamed.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',7,14,'That woman said, Today I fulfilled my vows <<that I made to the LORD>>. I gave a fellowship offering to the LORD. <<So I have some of the food at my house. Footnote: That food was part of the meat of the fellowship offering.>> See Leviticus 7:11-17.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',7,15,'So I came out <<from my house>> to meet you. I searched for you and found you!');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',7,16,'I covered my bed with sheets that have beautiful colors and that were brought from Egypt.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',7,17,'I sprinkled very expensive perfume, aloe, and cinnamon on my bed.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',7,18,'Come. Literal Alternate: Let''s drink love until the morning much. Dynamic Alternate: Let''s sleep with each other until the morning much. End of Alternates. Let''s enjoy our love!');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',7,19,'My husband isn''t at my house. He has traveled to a place that is far from here.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',7,20,'My husband took his bag of money with him. And he won''t return to our house until the day when the moon becomes biggest.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',7,21,'And so that woman persuaded that man to go with her. She caused that man to sleep with her by saying things that pleased him.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',7,22,'Suddenly that man followed that woman like an ox follows a person who will slaughter him or like a deer steps into a trap.');
