INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',12,26,'Primary: A righteous person advises his friend well. Alternate 1: A righteous person chooses his friend well. Literal Alternate: But evil people''s paths lead them to a wrong place. Dynamic Alternate: But the things that evil people do cause them to do more wrong things like a wrong path causes people to go to a wrong place.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',12,27,'Literal Alternate: A lazy person doesn''t roast the animals that he catches. Dynamic Alternate: A lazy person is like a person who doesn''t roast the animals that he catches. End of Alternates. But a person who works hard will get a lot of wealth.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',12,28,'Literal Alternate: Righteous actions lead life. Dynamic Alternate: A person who does righteous things will live. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: There isn''t death on that path. Dynamic Alternate: Those actions don''t lead death. End of Alternates. Footnote: Some manuscripts say, But evil actions lead death.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',13,1,'A wise son listens to the things that his father says when he tells a wise son about the sins him. But a person who mocks other people doesn''t listen to a person who rebukes him.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',13,2,'Literal Alternate: Because of the good fruit, a person''s lips he''ll enjoy good things. Dynamic Alternate: Because of the good things that a person says, he''ll enjoy good things. End of Alternates. But people who aren''t faithful really want to do violent things.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',13,3,'Literal Alternate: A person who guards his mouth protects his life. Dynamic Alternate: A person who speaks carefully protects himself <<from trouble>>. End of Alternates. But a person who says many things but doesn''t think about the things that he says will be destroyed by his words.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',13,4,'A lazy person wants things much. But he doesn''t get those things. But people who work hard will get all of the things that they desire.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',13,5,'A righteous person hates false things. But evil people''s neighbors are ashamed because they detest the things that they do.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',13,6,'Righteousness guards a person who does righteous things. But a sinner is destroyed by the evil actions him.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',13,7,'One person pretends to be rich. But he is poor. Another person pretends to be poor but he has a lot of wealth.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',13,8,'<<If a person kidnaps a rich person to get money,>> a rich person is able to pay his wealth to become free. But a person won''t kidnap a poor person to get money.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',13,9,'Good people are like a light that shines. But evil people are like a lamp that stops burning.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',13,10,'Proud people will oppose other people. But people who listen to advice are wise.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',13,11,'A person will stop having <<quickly>> money that he gets quickly. But the money that a person gets slowly and continuously will increase.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',13,12,'A person might hope that a certain thing will happen. Literal Alternate: If that person needs to much wait for that thing to happen, his heart will become sick. Dynamic Alternate: If that person needs to much wait for that thing to happen, he''ll become sad. End of Alternates. But when the thing that a person much wants to happen happens, he becomes very happy. Literal Alternate: He becomes happy like a person who eats a tree of life''s fruit is happy. Dynamic Alternate: That person becomes happy like a person who eats fruit of a tree that gives life is happy.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',13,13,'When a person despises an instruction, he causes him to have a lot of trouble. But the good things that a person who respects a command deserves will happen to him.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',13,14,'Literal Alternate: The things that a wise person teaches are a spring of life. Dynamic Alternate: The things that a wise person teaches cause people to live well like a spring causes people to have water. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: Those things will cause a person to avoid the traps of death. Dynamic Alternate: Those things will help a person escape from dangerous events that might cause him to die.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',13,15,'A wise person will be respected. But people who aren''t faithful will be destroyed by the actions of them.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',13,16,'Before each prudent person acts, he thinks about the actions of him carefully. But a foolish person''s actions show people that he is foolish.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',13,17,'An evil messenger will have trouble. Literal Alternate: But a faithful messenger causes people to be healthy. Dynamic Alternate: But a faithful messenger causes people to have good relationships with each other.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',13,18,'A person who ignores the words of a person who tells him about his sins will become poor. And he''ll be ashamed. But a person who listens to the words of a person who rebukes him will be honored by people.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',13,19,'When the things that a person wants to happen happen, he becomes happy. But foolish people refuse to stop doing evil things.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',13,20,'Literal Alternate: A person who walks with wise people will become wise. Dynamic Alternate: A person who is with wise people will become wise. End of Alternates. But a companion foolish people will suffer.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',13,21,'Literal Alternate: Trouble pursues sinners. Dynamic Alternate: Sinners will have trouble. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: But righteous people will receive a good reward. Dynamic Alternate: But good things will happen to righteous people.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',13,22,'Literal Alternate: A good person leaves things so that his children and his children could inherit them. Dynamic Alternate: A good person leaves things so that his descendants could inherit them. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: But a sinner stores his wealth for righteous people. Dynamic Alternate: But righteous people will get the wealth that a sinner has.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',13,23,'Poor people''s fields might produce a lot of food. But people who aren''t just take that food away <<often>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',13,24,'Literal Alternate: A person who doesn''t use a rod <<to punish his son>> hates him. Dynamic Alternate: A person who doesn''t punish his son doesn''t truly love him. End of Alternates. But a person who loves his son teaches him about the sins him <<by punishing a person''s son>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',13,25,'A righteous person eats until he is satisfied. Literal Alternate: But evil people''s stomachs are always hungry. Dynamic Alternate: But evil people are always hungry.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,1,'Literal Alternate: A wise woman builds her house. Dynamic Alternate: She causes the people who are in her family to have good relationships with each other. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: But a foolish woman destroys her house with her hands. Dynamic Alternate: But the things that a foolish woman does destroy her family.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,2,'Literal Alternate: A person who walks on straight paths fears the LORD. Dynamic Alternate: A person who does righteous things fears the LORD. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: But a person who walks on paths that aren''t straight despises the LORD. Dynamic Alternate: But a person who does things that aren''t honest despises the LORD.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,3,'Literal Alternate: Because of the proud words that come from a foolish person''s mouth, he''ll be hit with a rod. Dynamic Alternate: Because of the proud things that a foolish person says, he''ll be punished. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: But the words that come from wise people''s lips will protect them. Dynamic Alternate: But the things that wise people say will protect them.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,4,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,5,'A person who is faithful when he tells a judge about the things that he witnessed happening doesn''t lie. Literal Alternate: But a person who isn''t honest when he talks <<to a judge>> about the things that he witnessed happening lies like a person breathes. Dynamic Alternate: But a person who isn''t honest when he talks <<to a judge>> about the things that he witnessed happening lies.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,6,'A person who mocks won''t get wisdom even though he seeks it. But a sensible person will learn wise things easily.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,7,'Stay away from a foolish person. Literal Alternate: You won''t get knowledge from that person. Dynamic Alternate: You won''t learn <<useful>> things from that person.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,8,'A person''s prudent wisdom helps him know the things that he should do. But a foolish person''s foolish thoughts deceive him <<so he does wrong things>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,9,'Primary: Foolish people mock sacrifices that people offer <<to God>> because of their sins. Alternate 1: Foolish people don''t care about their sins. End of Alternates. But righteous people have good relationships with each other.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,10,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,11,'Evil people''s houses will fall. But righteous people''s tents will become bigger and better.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,12,'Some people think that they are doing right things. Literal Alternate: But finally those things lead to death. Dynamic Alternate: But finally those things cause those people to die.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,13,'Even if a person laughs, his heart might be sad. And later a person who rejoices now might be extremely sad.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,14,'The bad things that because of the actions of people who aren''t faithful, they deserve the things will happen to them. And the good things because of good people''s actions, they deserve the things will happen to them.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,15,'A person who doesn''t know many things will believe all of them. Literal Alternate: But he about he think step carefully. Dynamic Alternate: But he thinks carefully about the things he''ll do the things.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,16,'A wise person is careful so that he wouldn''t do evil things. But a foolish person is too confident and doesn''t control himself.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,17,'A person who becomes angry quickly does foolish things. And a person who plans to do evil things is hated.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,18,'Literal Alternate: People who don''t know many things get stupid actions. Dynamic Alternate: They do stupid things. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: But they get a hat knowledge. Dynamic Alternate: But they get the reward knowledge.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,19,'Evil people will kneel them. They''ll kneel at the Gates of Ephraim them.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,20,'Even if people live near poor people, they avoid them. But a rich person has many friends.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,21,'A person who thinks that he isn''t valuable does a bad thing. But he is blessed by the LORD.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,22,'Literal Alternate: Do people who plot to do evil things go on a wrong path? Dynamic Alternate: Do people who plot to do evil things do a wrong thing? End of Alternates. But people who plan to do good things for other people will be loved. And they''ll be trusted.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,23,'A person who works hard will earn good things. But lazy people who talk a lot <<but don''t work>> will become poor.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,24,'Literal Alternate: The hats wise people are their wealth. Dynamic Alternate: The rewards that wise people receive are their wealth. End of Alternates. But stupid people''s stupid actions cause them to become stupid more.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,25,'A person who says true things that are about the events that he witnessed happening saves people''s lives. But a person who lies about the events that he witnessed happening deceives people <<so the people who are judged aren''t treated fairly>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,26,'A person who fears the LORD will be very safe. And that person''s children will be also protected.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,27,'Literal Alternate: A person who fears the LORD will have a spring of life. Dynamic Alternate: A person who fears the LORD will live <<well>> like people who live near a spring of good water live <<well>>. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: And that person will avoid the traps of death. Dynamic Alternate: And he''ll escape from dangerous events that might cause him to die.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,28,'If a king rules many people, he has glory. But if a ruler rules few people, he''ll be destroyed.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,29,'A person who doesn''t become angry easily is wise. But a person who becomes angry quickly shows people that he is foolish.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,30,'Literal Alternate: A peaceful heart gives life to a person''s body. Dynamic Alternate: If a person is peaceful, he''ll be healthy. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: If a person wants the things that other people have, his bones will decay. Dynamic Alternate: If a person wants the things that other people have, he''ll die slowly.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,31,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,32,'An evil person is destroyed by his actions. Primary: A righteous person is safe because he is righteous. Alternate 1: But even if a righteous person dies, he is safe.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,33,'Literal Alternate: Wisdom rests in a sensible person''s heart. Dynamic Alternate: A sensible person''s heart is like a house where wisdom lives. End of Alternates. But wisdom isn''t in foolish people''s hearts.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,34,'A nation is great because its people are righteous. But if people sin, they''ll be ashamed.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',14,35,'A king''s wise servant pleases him. But a king will be extremely angry with a servant who causes him to be ashamed.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,1,'Literal Alternate: A person who gently speaks to other people causes them to turn away from wrath. Dynamic Alternate: He causes them to become less angry. End of Alternates. But a person who speaks to other people harshly causes them to become more angry.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,2,'Literal Alternate: The words wise people''s tongues cause knowledge <<wisdom>> to be attractive. Dynamic Alternate: The things that wise people say cause other people to want to learn about wisdom. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: But foolish things pour out from foolish people''s mouths. Dynamic Alternate: But foolish people say very many foolish things.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,3,'Literal Alternate: The LORD''s eyes are at each place. Dynamic Alternate: The LORD sees all things. End of Alternates. He watches evil people and good people.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,4,'Literal Alternate: A tongue that heals people is a tree of life. Dynamic Alternate: Kind words comfort people like a tree gives life <<by producing fruit>>. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: But an evil tongue crushes people''s spirits. Dynamic Alternate: But words that aren''t honest cause people to be sad and weak.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,5,'Literal Alternate: A foolish person refuses to accept the words of his father who tells a foolish person about his sins. Dynamic Alternate: A foolish person refuses to accept the words his parent who tells a foolish person about his sins. End of Alternates. But a person who accepts the words of a person who tells him that the things that he did are bad is prudent.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,6,'A righteous person''s house contains a lot of wealth. But the things that an evil person earns cause trouble there to be.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,7,'Literal Alternate: The words of a wise person''s lips spread knowledge. Dynamic Alternate: A wise person''s words cause people to know many valuable things. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: But the words a foolish person''s heart don''t spread knowledge. Dynamic Alternate: But a foolish person''s words don''t cause people to know things.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,8,'The LORD detests the sacrifices <<that evil people offer to him>>. But righteous people''s prayers please the LORD.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,9,'The LORD detests the things that evil people do. But he loves people who choose to do righteous things.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,10,'Literal Alternate: A person who abandons the right path will be punished harshly. Dynamic Alternate: A person who started doing wrong things will be punished harshly. End of Alternates. A person who hates the words of a person who tells him about his sins will die.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,11,'Literal Alternate: The LORD sees hell and Abaddon. Dynamic Alternate: He sees the place where dead people are. End of Alternates. So he certainly knows the thoughts humans'' hearts.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,12,'A person who mocks other people doesn''t like a person who tells him that the things that he did are bad. So a person won''t go to wise people <<to get advice>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,13,'The face of a person who has a joyful heart will look happy. Literal Alternate: But the very sad thoughts of a person who has pain in his heart will crush his spirit. Dynamic Alternate: But a sad person will look sad.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,14,'Literal Alternate: A sensible heart seeks knowledge. Dynamic Alternate: A sensible person tries to learn more things. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: But a foolish person''s mouth eats <<only>> foolish things. Dynamic Alternate: But foolish people listen to only foolish things.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,15,'Literal Alternate: All of the days people who suffer are bad. Dynamic Alternate: The life of a person who suffers is difficult. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: But a happy heart enjoys a feast continuously. Dynamic Alternate: But a happy person enjoys his life continuously like a person enjoys a feast.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,16,'One person has few things. But he fears the LORD. Another person has a lot of wealth. But he has a lot of trouble. The first person''s life is better than the second person''s life.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,17,'Literal Alternate: One person eats a meal of vegetables with people who love each other. Dynamic Alternate: He eats a simple meal with people who love each other. End of Alternates. Another person eats a fat young calf with people who hate each other. The first person''s life is better than the second person''s life.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,18,'A person who becomes angry quickly causes people to oppose each other. But a person who doesn''t become angry easily causes people to stop arguing with people.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,19,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,20,'Literal Alternate: A wise son causes his father to rejoice. Dynamic Alternate: A wise child causes his parents to rejoice. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: But a foolish man despises his mother. Dynamic Alternate: But a foolish person despises his parents.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,21,'Foolish people enjoy doing foolish things. Literal Alternate: But a sensible person stays on a straight path. Dynamic Alternate: But he continues doing right things.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,22,'If a person doesn''t get <<good>> advice, his plans will fail. But if many people advise that person well, his plans will succeed.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,23,'When a person replies <<to people>> well, he rejoices. It''s good that a person says the right words at the right time.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,24,'Literal Alternate: A wise person goes up on the path life. Dynamic Alternate: The things that a wise person does cause him to live for many years. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: That path helps that person not go down to hell. Dynamic Alternate: Those things help that person avoid the things that will cause him to die.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,25,'The LORD will destroy a proud person''s house. Literal Alternate: But he''ll protect a widow''s border. Dynamic Alternate: But he''ll protect a widow''s property.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,26,'The LORD detests an evil person''s thoughts. Literal Alternate: But he thinks that kind words are pure. Dynamic Alternate: But kind words please the LORD.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,27,'People who gain things by hurting other people destroy the families of them. Literal Alternate: But a person who hates a bribe will live. Dynamic Alternate: But a person who refuses to accept a bribe will live.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,28,'Literal Alternate: <<Before a righteous person speaks,>> his heart thinks about the words that it will say. Dynamic Alternate: <<Before a righteous person speaks,>> he thinks about the words that he''ll say. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: But evil things pour out from evil people''s mouths <<quickly>>. Dynamic Alternate: But evil people say very many evil things <<quickly>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,29,'Literal Alternate: The LORD is far from evil people. Dynamic Alternate: He doesn''t listen to evil people. End of Alternates. But he hears righteous people''s prayers.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,30,'Literal Alternate: When a person smiles, he causes other people''s hearts to rejoice. Dynamic Alternate: When a person smiles, he causes other people to rejoice. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: And good news <<that a person hears>> causes him to have healthy bones. Dynamic Alternate: And good news that a person hears causes him to feel good.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,31,'A person might tell you that the things that you did are bad so that you would live. If you listen to that person, you''ll be among the wise people.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,32,'Literal Alternate: A person who ignores the words of a person who tells him about his sins despises himself. Dynamic Alternate: A person who ignores the words of a person who tells him about his sins harms himself. End of Alternates. But a person who listens to the words of a person who tells him that the things that he did are bad will learn how to make good decisions.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',15,33,'A person becomes wise by fearing the LORD. And before a person is honored, he must not think that he is more important than other people.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,1,'Literal Alternate: Humans'' hearts make plans <<about the things that they''ll say>>. Dynamic Alternate: Humans make plans <<about the things that they''ll say>>. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: But the LORD causes people to say the things that come from their tongues. Dynamic Alternate: But he causes people to say the things that they say.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,2,'Literal Alternate: A person might think that all of the things that he does are pure. Dynamic Alternate: He might think that all of the things that he does are right. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: But the LORD weighs the reasons that people do things. Dynamic Alternate: But he judges the reasons that people do things.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,3,'Literal Alternate: Entrust to the LORD all of the things that you do. Dynamic Alternate: Whenever you do things, trust in the LORD. End of Alternates. Then the LORD will cause your plans to succeed.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,4,'The LORD has a reason for doing all of the things that he does. And he has prepared a day of many disaster for evil people.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,5,'Literal Alternate: The LORD detests people who have proud hearts. Dynamic Alternate: He detests proud people. End of Alternates. You should know that those people will certainly be punished.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,6,'Literal Alternate: The sins of a person who loves other people and is faithful will be covered. Dynamic Alternate: The sins of a person who loves other people and is faithful will be forgiven. End of Alternates. A person who fears the LORD will be protected from sins.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,7,'If a person lives so he pleases the LORD, his enemies will stop opposing him.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,8,'One person has few things. But he is righteous. Another person has a lot of wealth. But he isn''t honest. The first person''s life is better than the second person''s life.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,9,'Literal Alternate: A person''s heart plans his path. Dynamic Alternate: A person plans the things that he''ll do. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: But the LORD chooses the steps that person. Dynamic Alternate: But he chooses the things that actually the person does.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,10,'The words that come from a good king''s lips are the LORD''s message. The decisions that king are just.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,11,'Literal Alternate: Honest weights and honest devices that measure things belong to the LORD. Dynamic Alternate: The LORD causes people to use honest weights and honest devices that measure things. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: He made those weights and devices that measured things. Dynamic Alternate: Those weights and devices that measure things are right because the LORD caused people to make them so they are right.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,12,'<<Good>> kings detest evil actions. He continues ruling because people do right things.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,13,'Literal Alternate: People who have honest lips please <<good>> kings. Dynamic Alternate: Honest people please <<good>> kings. End of Alternates. <<Good>> kings know that people who say true things are valuable.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,14,'Literal Alternate: The wrath a king is the messenger death. Dynamic Alternate: An angry king is able to cause people to die. End of Alternates. So a wise person will cause that king to become less angry.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,15,'Literal Alternate: When a king smiles, he gives life to people. Dynamic Alternate: When a king is happy, people are able to live for many years. End of Alternates. When a king is pleased with people, the <<kind>> actions him are like a cloud that brings rain a spring <<when the crops need it it>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,16,'It''s good that a person gets gold. But it''s better that a person gets wisdom. It''s good that a person gets silver. But it''s better that a person understands wisdom.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,17,'Literal Alternate: The wide road righteous people avoids evil actions. Dynamic Alternate: Righteous people avoid evil actions like a person goes straight on a wide road. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: A person who guards his path preserves his life. Dynamic Alternate: A person who is careful about the things that he does preserves his life.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,18,'A proud person will be destroyed. Literal Alternate: A person who has a proud heart will fall down. Dynamic Alternate: A person who thinks that he is better than other people will have a disaster.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,19,'One person is among poor people. But he is humble. Another person is among proud people and shares the things that they take from their enemies. The first person''s life is better than the second person''s life.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,20,'A person who listens to an instruction will succeed. And a person who trusts in the LORD is blessed.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,21,'Literal Alternate: People know that a person who has a wise heart is sensible. Dynamic Alternate: People know that a wise person is sensible. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: And kind words better persuade people to make good decisions. Dynamic Alternate: And a person who speaks graciously better persuades people to make good decisions.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,22,'Wisdom is a spring of life that is for the person who has it. But foolish people''s foolish actions cause them to be punished.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,23,'Literal Alternate: A wise person''s heart teaches his mouth. Dynamic Alternate: A wise person''s wisdom helps him know the things that he should say. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: And that person''s lips persuade people to make good decisions. Dynamic Alternate: And that person''s words persuade people to make good decisions.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,24,'Kind words are like honey. Literal Alternate: Those words are sweet Literal Alternate: And cause people''s bones to be healthy. Dynamic Alternate: Those words cause people to be happy and healthy.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,25,'Some people think that they are doing right things. Literal Alternate: But finally those things lead death. Dynamic Alternate: But finally those things cause those people to die.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,26,'A worker works because he wants to eat. He works harder because he is hungry.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,27,'A person who isn''t valuable plots to do evil things. Literal Alternate: A fire that is burning is on that person''s lips. Dynamic Alternate: That person''s words are like a fire that is burning.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,28,'A perverse person causes people to oppose each other. And a person who talks about the bad things that people did causes people to stop being their friends.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,29,'A violent person tempts his neighbor. Literal Alternate: And that violent person leads that neighbor on a path that isn''t good. Dynamic Alternate: And that violent person causes that neighbor to sin.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,30,'<<An evil person makes a sign so that his friends would see it.>> A person who closes one of his eyes for about a second is plotting to do perverse things. A person who causes his lips to each other is ready to do evil things.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,31,'An <<old>> person''s gray hair is a beautiful crown. Literal Alternate: That person gets that crown by living well. Dynamic Alternate: He lives for many years because he is righteous.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,32,'The life of a person who doesn''t become angry quickly is better than the life a strong soldier. The life of a person who controls himself is better than the life of a person who captures a city.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',16,33,'A person might throw a lot <<to make a decision>>. Literal Alternate: But the LORD chooses the answer. Dynamic Alternate: But he chooses the things the things will happen.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',17,1,'One person eats <<only>> a dry piece of bread. But the people who are in that person''s house are peaceful. Another person eats a feast. But the people who are in that person''s house angrily argue with each other. The first person''s life is better than the second person''s life.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',17,2,'A wise servant will rule a son who causes his family to be ashamed. That servant will share the things that the other sons inherit.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',17,3,'People test silver and gold by using a furnace. Literal Alternate: But the LORD tests people''s hearts. Dynamic Alternate: But he tests people.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',17,4,'Literal Alternate: An evil person listens to evil lips. Dynamic Alternate: An evil person listens to the evil things that people say. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: A person who lies listens to a cruel tongue. Dynamic Alternate: A person who lies listens to cruel words.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',17,5,'A person who mocks a poor person despises God, who made a poor person. A person who rejoices when another person has a disaster will be punished.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',17,6,'Literal Alternate: Old people''s children''s children are the crowns them. Dynamic Alternate: Old people <<usually>> are proud of their children''s children. Dynamic Alternate: They are like kings who wear crowns. End of Alternates. And children usually are proud of their parents.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',17,7,'Literal Alternate: It isn''t appropriate that a foolish person says excellent words. Dynamic Alternate: People don''t expect him to say excellent words. End of Alternates. It''s much less appropriate that a ruler lies.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',17,8,'A person who gives money to another person to cause another him to sin thinks that it''s like a stone magic. He thinks that that money will cause him to always succeed.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',17,9,'Literal Alternate: A person who covers sins seeks love. Dynamic Alternate: A person who wants to love other people and they love him forgives their sins. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: But a person who repeatedly talks about another person''s sin separates good people from their friends. Dynamic Alternate: But a person who repeatedly talks about a bad thing that another person did causes people to stop being good friends.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',17,10,'Literal Alternate: When a sensible person is told that the thing that he did is bad, he learns a lesson more than when a foolish person is whipped one hundred times, he learns a lesson. Dynamic Alternate: When a sensible person is told that the thing that he did is bad, he learns a lesson more than when a foolish person is whipped harshly, he learns a lesson.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',17,11,'An evil person desires to rebel against people. A cruel messenger will be sent so that he would punish that evil person.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',17,12,'If a female bear doesn''t continue having her young bears, it''s bad that a person meets her. But it''s worse that a person meets a foolish person who is doing foolish things.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',17,13,'Literal Alternate: Trouble will always be in the house of a person who sins against people who treat him well. Dynamic Alternate: Bad things will always happen to the family of a person who sins against people who treat him well.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',17,14,'When water starts pouring out <<from a container>>, it continues falling. And when people start arguing with each other, they continue arguing with each other. So before people become angry, stop arguing with them.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',17,15,'One judge declares that a guilty person is innocent. Another judge condemns a person who is innocent. The LORD detests both of those judges.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',17,16,'Literal Alternate: Why should a foolish person have money in his hand so that he could buy wisdom? Dynamic Alternate: Why should he try to buy wisdom? End of Alternates. He isn''t able to understand wisdom.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',17,17,'A friend continues always loving people. Literal Alternate: And a brother is born so that when his family has trouble, he could help them. Dynamic Alternate: And people are in a family so that when they have trouble, they could help them.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',17,18,'Perhaps a person borrowed money from another person. And perhaps a neighbor of the person who borrowed money agreed if he hadn''t been able to return it, to pay it to the person who loaned it to that person. And the neighbor who made that promise shook the hand of the person who loaned the money to that person <<to show the person that he agreed to do this>>. The neighbor who made that promise is foolish.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',17,19,'A person who likes sinning likes causing people to oppose each other. Literal Alternate: A person who builds a high gate invites a disaster to happen. Dynamic Alternate: A person who proudly speaks will probably have trouble.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',17,20,'Literal Alternate: A person who has a perverse heart won''t succeed. Dynamic Alternate: A perverse person won''t succeed. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: A person who has a perverse tongue will have trouble. Dynamic Alternate: A person who deceives people will have a disaster.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',17,21,'A person who has a foolish son will be very sad. A foolish son''s father and his mother won''t rejoice.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',17,22,'Literal Alternate: A happy heart is good medicine. Dynamic Alternate: A person becomes healthy because he is happy like a person who gets medicine becomes healthy. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: But if a person''s spirit is crushed, his bones will become dry. Dynamic Alternate: But if a person is very sad, he''ll become weak.');
