INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',18,3,'If a person does a bad thing, other people won''t respect him. When that person becomes ashamed, they''ll mock him.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',18,4,'Literal Alternate: The words of a wise person''s mouth are deep water. Dynamic Alternate: A person''s wise words are like deep water. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: The spring wisdom is a stream that flows. Dynamic Alternate: A wise person says wise things like good water flows from a spring.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',18,5,'Literal Alternate: It isn''t good that an evil person is treated well. Dynamic Alternate: It''s bad that a guilty person is punished. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: Then the righteous person isn''t treated justly. Dynamic Alternate: Then they aren''t treated justly.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',18,6,'Literal Alternate: A foolish person''s lips cause people to oppose him. Dynamic Alternate: The words that a foolish person says cause people to oppose him. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: That person''s mouth invites people to beat him. Dynamic Alternate: Those words might cause people to beat him.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',18,7,'Literal Alternate: A foolish person''s mouth causes him to be destroyed. Dynamic Alternate: The things that a foolish person says cause him to be destroyed. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: That person''s lips are the snare <<that causes him to die>> his soul. Dynamic Alternate: That person''s words are like a snare that will cause him to die.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',18,8,'The words of a person who talks about the bad things that other people did are like pieces of food that taste good. Literal Alternate: Those words go to the inner part of a person. Dynamic Alternate: People remember those words. Dynamic Alternate: And they think about those words.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',18,9,'Literal Alternate: A person who doesn''t work hard is a brother of a person who destroys things. Dynamic Alternate: A person who doesn''t work hard is like a person who destroys things.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',18,10,'Literal Alternate: The LORD''s name is a strong tower. Dynamic Alternate: The LORD protects people like a strong tower protects people. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: <<When there is danger,>> a righteous person runs to that tower. Dynamic Alternate: <<When there is danger,>> a righteous person prays immediately to the LORD like when an enemy attacks people, they run to a strong tower. End of Alternates. And that person becomes safe.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',18,11,'A rich person''s wealth is his city that has high walls. Literal Alternate: That person imagines the high walls will always protect him. Dynamic Alternate: He imagines that wealth will always protect him like high walls protect people from enemies.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',18,12,'Literal Alternate: A person who has a proud heart will be destroyed. Dynamic Alternate: A proud person will be destroyed. End of Alternates. But a humble person will be honored.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',18,13,'A person who replies before he hears <<all of>> the things that another person is saying is foolish. And he''ll be ashamed.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',18,14,'A person''s spirit is able even if the body him becomes sick, to live. Literal Alternate: But if a person''s spirit is crushed, how is a person able to continue living? Dynamic Alternate: But if a person is extremely sad, he won''t have hope.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',18,15,'Dynamic Alternate: A sensible person''s heart learns wisdom. End of Alternates. A sensible person learns wisdom. Literal Alternate: For a wise person''s ear seeks wisdom. Dynamic Alternate: For a wise person listens to people to learn wisdom.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',18,16,'Literal Alternate: A gift opens doors for a person. Dynamic Alternate: A person is able to do the things that he wants to do because he gives a gift to an important person. End of Alternates. Because of that gift, a person is able to meet great people.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',18,17,'The first person who speaks about something that happened seems to say true things. Then another person comes and asks the first person questions. <<And people find out that the thing that happened is more complicated.>>');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',18,18,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',18,19,'It''s difficult for people to capture a city that has high walls. But it''s more difficult for a person to become a friend of a person that he has insulted again. Literal Alternate: Are like a gate that has a bar. Literal Alternate: The gate is on a building that has strong walls. Dynamic Alternate: Prevent people from becoming <<their>> friends like a bar that is on a gate prevents people from entering a building that has strong walls.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',18,20,'Literal Alternate: A <<wise>> person''s stomach will be satisfied by the fruit his mouth. Dynamic Alternate: Wise words will satisfy a <<wise>> person like a delicious meal satisfies a person. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: A <<wise>> person will be satisfied by the words that his lips produce. Dynamic Alternate: The things that a <<wise>> person says will satisfy him.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',18,21,'Literal Alternate: The words the tongue have the power life and death. Dynamic Alternate: The things that people say are able to cause people to continue living or to die. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: And people who love the words the tongue will eat the fruit them it. Dynamic Alternate: The people who like talking a lot will be affected by the things that the people who like talking a lot said. End of Alternates. So be <<careful>> about the things that you say.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',18,22,'Literal Alternate: It''s good that a man finds a wife. Dynamic Alternate: It''s good that a man meets a woman and that he marries her. End of Alternates. The LORD is pleased with that man.');
