INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',19,1,'One person is poor. But he is blameless. A second person is foolish. Literal Alternate: And the words of that person''s lips are perverse. Dynamic Alternate: And that person says perverse things. End of Alternates. The life of the first person is better than the life of the second person.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',19,2,'Literal Alternate: It isn''t good that a person eagerly does things without knowledge. Dynamic Alternate: It isn''t good that a person eagerly does things but that he doesn''t think about the things that he does. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: A person who acts too quickly won''t find the right path. Dynamic Alternate: A person who acts too quickly will make mistakes.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',19,3,'');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',19,4,'Literal Alternate: Wealth attracts many <<new>> friends. Dynamic Alternate: If a person is rich, many people will want to be his friends. End of Alternates. But a poor person''s friend will avoid him.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',19,5,'A person who lies <<in a court>> will certainly be punished. Literal Alternate: And a person who pours false things out won''t escape. Dynamic Alternate: And a person who lies won''t escape.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',19,6,'Many people try to cause important officials to help them. Literal Alternate: And every person is a friend of a person who regularly gives gifts to other people. Dynamic Alternate: And every person wants to be a friend of a person who regularly gives gifts to other people.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',19,7,'All of a poor person''s relatives despise him. So people who are <<only>> that person''s friends will certainly abandon him. Literal Alternate: Those friends are like people who aren''t there even though that person pursues them to beg them to help him. Dynamic Alternate: They won''t listen to that person even though he pursues them to beg them to help him.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',19,8,'Literal Alternate: A person who gets wisdom loves his life. Dynamic Alternate: A person who becomes wise cares about his life. End of Alternates. A person who wants to understand wisdom will succeed.');
