INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',19,19,'Let a person who becomes extremely angry be disciplined. If you rescue that person <<from the thing that will happen to him>>, you''ll need to rescue him again.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',19,20,'Listen to <<wise people''s>> advice and accept the words of a person who tells you about your sins. Then you''ll become wise eventually.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',19,21,'Literal Alternate: A person has many plans in his heart. Dynamic Alternate: He has many plans. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: But the LORD''s plan will stand. Dynamic Alternate: But the things that the LORD wants will happen.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',19,22,'Literal Alternate: A person wants to faithfully love him. Dynamic Alternate: He wants to be loyal. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: So the life of a poor person <<who tells the truth>> is better than it. Dynamic Alternate: So people will like him more than they''ll like him.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',19,23,'A person who fears the LORD will live <<for many years>>. He''ll be content. And trouble won''t bother that person.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',19,24,'Literal Alternate: A lazy person will bury his lazy hand in the food that is on a plate. Dynamic Alternate: He''ll put his hand into the food that is on a plate. End of Alternates. But he won''t take that food to his mouth <<because he is extremely lazy to eat it>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',19,25,'Whip a person who laughs at wisdom. Then perhaps the people who don''t know many things will become clever more. But rebuke a sensible person. Then that person will gain knowledge.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',19,26,'Literal Alternate: A son who treats his father badly and forces his mother to leave her house will cause his whole family to become ashamed of him. Dynamic Alternate: A son who takes his parents'' property and forces them to leave their house will cause his whole family to become ashamed of him.');
