INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',20,13,'If you <<too much>> enjoy sleeping, you''ll become poor. Literal Alternate: Open your eyes. Dynamic Alternate: Continue being awake. End of Alternates. <<And do your work.>> Then you''ll have more than enough food <<that you''ll be able to eat>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',20,14,'Literal Alternate: A person says that the price that he paid for something was very bad. Dynamic Alternate: He says that the price that he paid was too high. End of Alternates. But after that person leaves <<the person that he bought that thing from>>, he proudly speaks <<about that price>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',20,15,'There is <<a lot of>> gold. And there are many jewels that cost a lot of money. Literal Alternate: But lips of knowledge are more precious <<than those things>>. Dynamic Alternate: But a sensible person''s words are more precious <<than those things>>.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',20,16,'Perhaps a person that you don''t know borrowed money from you. But another person agreed if the person who borrowed that money wasn''t able to return it, to pay it to you. Literal Alternate: Take the coat of the person who made that promise. Dynamic Alternate: Take a valuable thing from the person who made that promise. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: And keep that coat so that if the person who borrowed that money isn''t able to pay it to you, that person would pay it to you. Dynamic Alternate: And keep that thing so that if the person who borrowed that money isn''t able to pay it to you, that person would pay it to you.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',20,17,'Literal Alternate: The food that a person gets by cheating other people might taste sweet. Dynamic Alternate: The things that a person gets by cheating other people might please him like sweet food pleases people. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: But later that person will have stones and sand in his mouth. Dynamic Alternate: But later that person will have trouble. Dynamic Alternate: He''ll be like a person who has stones and sand in his mouth.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',20,18,'If you seek <<wise>> advice, <<and if you follow it,>> your plans will succeed. So if you fight a war, get <<good>> advice.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',20,19,'A person who lies causes people to know secrets <<that they shouldn''t know>>. Literal Alternate: So avoid a person who talks too much. Dynamic Alternate: So avoid a person who says things that he shouldn''t say.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',20,20,'Literal Alternate: If a person insults his father or his mother, the lamp him will be caused by the LORD in darkness will stop burning. Dynamic Alternate: A person who insults his father or his mother will die. Dynamic Alternate: That person''s life will be like a lamp that was caused by him stopped burning so there is total darkness.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',20,21,'Finally wealth that a person gets quickly because after his parents died, he received it will help him.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',20,22,'Don''t say, I''ll punish you because of the evil things that you did to me! Wait for the LORD to act. Literal Alternate: Then the LORD will help you. Dynamic Alternate: Then the LORD will cause things to be right.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',20,23,'Literal Alternate: The LORD detests different weights. Dynamic Alternate: He detests the actions of people who don''t honestly measure things because they use different weights <<to cheat them>>. End of Alternates. Literal Alternate: And devices that weigh things and aren''t honest don''t please the LORD. Dynamic Alternate: People who use scales that don''t honestly weigh things cause the LORD to become angry.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',20,24,'Literal Alternate: The LORD chooses a person''s steps. Dynamic Alternate: He chooses the things that a person does. End of Alternates. So how is a person able to understand his path?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Proverbs',20,25,'Before a person makes a promise, he should think about the things that he''ll say. Literal Alternate: A person who carelessly says, That thing is holy <<for the LORD>> Is like an animal that is caught in a trap. Dynamic Alternate: A person who carelessly promises he''ll give something to the LORD is like an animal that is caught in a trap. End of Alternates. <<That person might not be able to change into his words.>>');
