INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',1,1,'Title: Elimelech and Naomi move from Bethlehem to Moab. When judges were ruling Israel, there was a famine in Israel. A certain man was from Bethlehem, which was in Judah. That man, his wife, and his two sons moved from Bethlehem to a country named Moab to live there for a few years.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',1,2,'That man''s name was Elimelech. Elimelech''s wife''s name was Naomi. One son''s name was Mahlon. And the other son''s name was Kilion. Elimelech and Naomi were in Ephrah''s clan. That family was living in a town named Bethlehem, which was in Judah. But they went to a country named Moab and lived there.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',1,3,'Later Elimelech, who was Naomi''s husband, died. So Naomi lived with her two sons.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',1,4,'Those sons married women who were from Moab. One son married a woman named Orpah. And the other son married a woman named Ruth. That family continued living in Moab for about ten years.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',1,5,'Then Mahlon and Kilion also died. So Naomi didn''t have her sons or her husband.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',1,6,'While Naomi was living in Moab, she heard that the LORD was taking care of his people who were in Israel. The LORD was giving food to those people. So Naomi prepared to return to Bethlehem. Naomi''s daughters-in-law also prepared to go to Bethlehem with her.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',1,7,'Then Naomi and her two daughters-in-law left the place where they were living and started walking on the road that led to Judah.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',1,8,'But Naomi said to her two daughters-in-law, My daughters, return to your mothers'' houses. May the LORD be kind to you like you were kind to your dead husbands and me.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',1,9,'May the LORD give new husbands to you so that you can rest. Then Naomi kissed her daughters-in-law. And Naomi and her daughters-in-law wept loudly.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',1,10,'Then Naomi''s daughters-in-law said to her, We''ll certainly go to your people with you.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',1,11,'But Naomi said, My daughters, return to your houses. Why should you come with me? Will I give birth to more sons who will become your husbands?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',1,12,'My daughters, return to your parents'' houses. I''m not able to marry another man because I''m too old. I don''t hope to marry another man. Even if I marry a man tonight, and even if I give birth to sons, will you wait for them to grow up?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',1,13,'Won''t you marry other men? My daughters, I''m very bitter because the LORD treated me badly!');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',1,14,'Then Naomi and her daughters-in-law wept again loudly. Then Orpah kissed Naomi and said goodbye to her. But Ruth hugged Naomi.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',1,15,'Naomi said to Ruth, Orpah is returning to her people and her gods. Go with Orpah.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',1,16,'But Ruth said to Naomi, Don''t tell me to leave you. Allow me to go with you. I''ll go to the place where you''ll go. And I will stay at the place where you''ll stay. Your people will become my people. And your God will be my God.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',1,17,'I''ll die at the place where you''ll die. And I will be buried there. I swear to the LORD that I''ll stay with you until I die. If I don''t keep this promise, the LORD should punish me severely.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',1,18,'Naomi realized that Ruth decided to go with her. So Naomi stopped arguing with Ruth.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',1,19,'Then Naomi and Ruth continued traveling to Bethlehem. When Naomi and Ruth arrived in Bethlehem, the people who were living there became excited. The women who were living in Bethlehem asked each other, Is this woman Naomi?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',1,20,'But Naomi said to those people, Don''t call me ''Naomi''. Call me ''Mara'' because the LORD Almighty caused me to become very bitter. But Mara means ''bitter''.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',1,21,'Then Naomi said, When I left Bethlehem, I had many good things. But the LORD took those things away from me. So why should you call me ''Naomi''? The LORD caused me to suffer. The LORD Almighty caused bad things to happen to me.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',1,22,'So Naomi returned from Moab. And Ruth, who was from Moab, went to Bethlehem with Naomi. Naomi and Ruth arrived in Bethlehem during the time when people started harvesting barley.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',2,1,'Title: Ruth meets Boaz. Naomi had a relative named Boaz. Boaz and Elimelech were in the same clan. People respected Boaz highly. And Boaz was rich.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',2,2,'One day Ruth, who was from Moab, said to Naomi, Let me go to the fields. I''ll pick up barley that will be left in the fields. I''ll work behind people who will be kind to me. Naomi said to Ruth, My daughter, go.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',2,3,'So Ruth left and entered a field. She started walking behind some people who were harvesting barley. And she picked up the barley that those people didn''t gather. She was working in a field that belonged to Boaz. Boaz and Elimelech were in the same clan.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',2,4,'Then Boaz arrived from Bethlehem. He said to the people who were harvesting the barley, May the LORD be with you! And those people said to Boaz, May the LORD bless you!');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',2,5,'Then Boaz asked the leader of the workers, To whom does that young woman belong?');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',2,6,'That leader answered Boaz, That woman is from Moab. That woman came from Moab here with Naomi.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',2,7,'That woman said to me, Please let me glean behind the workers who are harvesting barley. And let me gather barley between the sheaves. That woman came into this field in this morning and worked continuously. She rested for a few minutes in the shelter.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',2,8,'Then Boaz said to Ruth, My daughter, listen to me. Don''t go to another field to glean. Don''t leave this field. But stay in this field with the women who are working for me.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',2,9,'Watch the field where the men are harvesting barley. And follow the women. I told the men not to touch you. Whenever you become thirsty, go to those containers. And drink the water that is in those containers that the men filled.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',2,10,'Then Ruth bowed to Boaz and put her face to the ground. Then she asked Boaz, Why are you kind to me? I''m a foreigner.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',2,11,'Boaz answered Ruth, People told me about all of the things that you did for your mother-in-law after your husband died. You left your father, your mother, and the land where you were born. And you came to this land to live with people that you didn''t know.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',2,12,'May the LORD bless you because you did good things. And may he, who is the God of Israel, reward you. You came to the LORD like a young bird comes to its mother. The mother''s wings protect that young bird.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',2,13,'Then Ruth said to Boaz, My master, I hope that you''ll continue treating me very kindly. Although I''m not one of your servants, you comforted me. And you spoke kindly to me.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',2,14,'When Boaz and his workers started eating, he said to Ruth, Come here and eat bread. You may dip the bread in this vinegar. So Ruth sat down beside the workers. Then Boaz gave Ruth some grain that was roasted. Ruth ate that grain until she was full. And she still had more grain.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',2,15,'Then Ruth stood up to start gleaning again. Then Boaz commanded the men who were working for him, Let Ruth gather the barley that is near the sheaves and don''t tell her to stop gleaning.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',2,16,'And pull some stalks out of the sheaves for Ruth and drop them on the ground so that she could pick them up. And don''t tell Ruth to stop gathering barley.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',2,17,'So Ruth gleaned in that field until the evening. After Ruth threshed the barley, she had about 30 pounds of barley.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',2,18,'Then Ruth carried the barley to the town. And Ruth''s mother-in-law saw the barley that she gathered. Ruth also showed Naomi the extra food that she didn''t eat earlier. And Ruth gave that food to Naomi.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',2,19,'Ruth''s mother-in-law asked her, Where did you glean today? Where did you work? May the LORD bless the man who helped you! Then Ruth told her mother-in-law about the owner of the field where she worked. Ruth said, The name of the man that I worked with today is Boaz.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',2,20,'Naomi said to her daughter-in-law, May the LORD bless Boaz! The LORD is kind to living people and dead people. Naomi also said to Ruth, Boaz is our close relative. Boaz is one of our guardian-redeemers.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',2,21,'Then Ruth, who was from Moab, said, Boaz also said to me, Stay with my workers until they finish harvesting all of my grain.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',2,22,'Then Naomi said to Ruth, who was her daughter-in-law, My daughter, you should continue working with the women who work for Boaz. If you work in another man''s field, people might hurt you.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',2,23,'So Ruth continued working with the women who worked for Boaz. She gathered barley until the workers finished harvesting the barley. Then she gathered wheat until the workers finished harvesting the wheat. And she lived with her mother-in-law.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',3,1,'Title: Ruth meets Boaz at the threshing floor. One day Ruth''s mother-in-law named Naomi said to Ruth, My daughter, I have to find a person who will take care of you well.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',3,2,'Recently you were working with the women who work for Boaz. Boaz is our relative. Boaz will be winnowing barley at the threshing floor tonight.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',3,3,'Therefore, wash yourself and put perfume on your body. Then put your best clothes on. Then go to the threshing floor. But don''t let Boaz see you. Boaz will eat and drink. Wait for Boaz to finish eating and to finish drinking.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',3,4,'When Boaz lies down, watch him carefully so that you can see the place where he is lying. Later go to Boaz and lift the blanket that is on his feet. Then lie down. Then Boaz will tell you to do certain things.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',3,5,'Then Ruth said to Naomi, I''ll do all of the things that you said.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',3,6,'So Ruth went to the threshing floor and did all of the things that her mother-in-law told her to do.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',3,7,'Boaz ate some food and drank some wine. Then he was happy and lay down beside the pile of the barley. Later Ruth came to Boaz quietly and lifted the blanket that was on his feet. Then she lay down.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',3,8,'At about midnight Boaz woke up and turned around. Then he saw a woman lying beside his feet!');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',3,9,'Boaz asked that woman, Who are you? Ruth said, I''m your servant named Ruth. Please cover me, your servant, with the corner of your robe because you''re our family''s guardian-redeemer.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',3,10,'Then Boaz said, My daughter, may the LORD bless you. Previously you were kind. But you''re very kind now. You didn''t try to marry a young man. You didn''t search for a rich young man or a poor young man.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',3,11,'My daughter, don''t be afraid. I''ll do for you all of the things that you asked me to do. All of the people who are living in this town know that you''re a very good woman.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',3,12,'I''m our family''s guardian-redeemer. But another man is a closer guardian-redeemer than me.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',3,13,'Stay here tonight. In the morning I''ll talk to that man. If that man wants to become your guardian-redeemer, I''ll have to let him redeem you. But if that man doesn''t want to become your guardian-redeemer, I''ll certainly redeem you. I swear to the LORD that I''ll redeem you. So lie until the morning here.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',3,14,'So Ruth lay until the morning near Boaz''s feet. She got up while it still was too dark so that people couldn''t recognize each other. Then Boaz said, People must not know that a woman came to the threshing floor.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',3,15,'Then Boaz also said to Ruth, Bring to me the shawl that you''re wearing and hold it for me. Then he poured about fifty pounds of barley on Ruth''s shawl. Then he put the shawl on Ruth''s back. Then he returned to the town.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',3,16,'Then Ruth came to her mother-in-law. Naomi asked Ruth, My daughter, what happened? Then Ruth told Naomi about all of the things that Boaz did for her.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',3,17,'Ruth said, Boaz gave about fifty pounds of barley to me and said, Take this gift to your mother-in-law.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',3,18,'Then Naomi said, My daughter, wait until you hear about the things that Boaz will do. Today Boaz will certainly talk to that man.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',4,1,'Title: Boaz marries Ruth. Boaz went to the town gate and sat down near it. Then the guardian-redeemer that Boaz talked about walked near the gate. So Boaz said to that man, My friend, come here and sit down. So that man came to Boaz and sat down.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',4,2,'Then Boaz asked ten old men who were leaders of that town to come there. He said to those men, Sit down here. So those ten old men sat down.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',4,3,'Then Boaz said to the guardian-redeemer, Naomi returned from Moab. Our relative named Elimelech owned some land. Now Naomi wants to sell that land.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',4,4,'So I thought that I should tell you about these things. And I thought that I should suggest to you that you redeem that land. I''m telling these things to you in front of the people who are sitting here and in front of these ten leaders of our town. If you want to redeem that land, redeem it. But if you don''t want to redeem that land, tell me. Only you have the right to redeem that land. But if you don''t want to redeem that land, I have the right to redeem it. Then that man said, I''ll redeem that land.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',4,5,'Then Boaz said, On the day when you buy that land from Naomi, you have to also marry Ruth, who is from Moab. Ruth was Elimelech''s son''s wife. But Elimelech''s son is dead. You''ll protect the dead man''s name and his property by marrying Ruth.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',4,6,'The guardian-redeemer said, Then I''m not able to redeem that land. If I marry Ruth, and if she gives birth to a son, my sons might receive less land from me. So you redeem that land for yourself. I''m not able to redeem that land.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',4,7,'(In those days the people who lived in Israel had a custom. If one person allowed another person to redeem land, or if one person gave land to another person, that person took off his sandal. And he gave that sandal to the other person. Then other people knew that the other person owned that land.)');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',4,8,'So the guardian-redeemer said to Boaz, You buy that land. Then the guardian-redeemer took off his sandal.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',4,9,'Then Boaz announced to the ten old men who were leaders of that town and the other people who were there, Today you witnessed me buying from Naomi all of the land that Elimelech, Kilion, and Mahlon owned.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',4,10,'I''ll also marry Ruth, who is from Moab. Ruth was Mahlon''s wife. I''ll do these things to protect the dead man''s name and his property. Therefore, that man''s relatives and the people who live in his town won''t forget about his name. Today you witnessed me doing these things!');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',4,11,'Then those ten old men and all of the people who were at the gate said, We witnessed you doing these things. May the LORD cause the woman that you''ll marry to become like Rachel and Leah. And may he cause that woman to give birth to many children like Rachel and Leah gave birth to the children who became the Israelites. And may you become powerful in Ephrathah. And may all of the people who live in Bethlehem know about you.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',4,12,'May the LORD give many children to you and this young woman. And may your family become like Perez''s family. Tamar gave birth to Perez for Judah.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',4,13,'So Boaz married Ruth. When Boaz slept with Ruth, the LORD caused her to become pregnant. Then Ruth gave birth to a son.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',4,14,'The women who were living in Bethlehem said to Naomi, We praise the LORD. The LORD provided for you a person who will protect Elimelech''s family and his land. May all of the people who are living in Israel know about this child!');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',4,15,'When you were young, you were happy. This child will cause you to become happy again. And when you become old, he''ll take care of you. Your daughter-in-law, who loves you, gave birth to this son. And she is better than seven sons for you.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',4,16,'Then Naomi held that baby and took care of him.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',4,17,'The women who were living near Naomi said, Naomi has a son! The women named that baby Obed. Obed became Jesse''s father. And Jesse became David''s father.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',4,18,'These people are Perez''s descendants. Perez was Hezron''s father.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',4,19,'Hezron was Ram''s father. Ram was Amminadab''s father.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',4,20,'Amminadab was Nahshon''s father. Nahshon was Salmon''s father.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',4,21,'Salmon was Boaz''s father. Boaz was Obed''s father.');
INSERT INTO English VALUES('Ruth',4,22,'Obed was Jesse''s father. And Jesse was David''s father.');
